1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:18,151
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:18,218 --> 00:00:21,521
The best chefs in Korea will
turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:21,588 --> 00:00:23,890
The classy cooking show has returned.

4
00:00:23,957 --> 00:00:27,160
-<i>Chef & My Fridge!</i>
-<i>My Fridge!</i>

5
00:00:29,062 --> 00:00:30,997
Hello. It's nice to have you here.

6
00:00:31,064 --> 00:00:33,299
-It's great to be here.
-It's refreshing and new.

7
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:36,669
Many people were probably surprised

8
00:00:36,736 --> 00:00:40,006
to see my partner here today.

9
00:00:40,073 --> 00:00:43,643
Jung-hwan had to take
a sudden sick leave today.

10
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:45,045
-Yes.
-Yes.

11
00:00:45,111 --> 00:00:48,181
He has been actively engaged
in many different areas recently,

12
00:00:48,248 --> 00:00:50,683
so it must've taken a toll on his body.

13
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:52,352
-Gosh.
-Yes, that's why

14
00:00:52,419 --> 00:00:56,322
she's here to fill in for him,
a previous fridge owner, actually.

15
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:58,858
Lee Eun-ji is back here
as my partner today.

16
00:00:58,925 --> 00:01:01,928
It's great to be here. Thank you.

17
00:01:01,995 --> 00:01:05,432
-As soon as Eun-ji said okay…
-Yes?

18
00:01:05,498 --> 00:01:07,200
…and agreed to come on the show,

19
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:10,403
we had some protests
from Kang-rok and Jong-won.

20
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:12,472
-They protested? Why?
-Why?

21
00:01:12,539 --> 00:01:14,441
I missed Rok and Won so much.

22
00:01:14,507 --> 00:01:17,477
-The Rok and Won's love triangle.
-Yes.

23
00:01:17,544 --> 00:01:19,345
How did you feel, Chef Jong-won?

24
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:21,781
That episode was my first time on TV.

25
00:01:22,549 --> 00:01:23,950
-What did you say?
-Son Jong…

26
00:01:24,017 --> 00:01:25,752
-Eun-ji!
-Son?

27
00:01:25,819 --> 00:01:27,320
Here, this is for you.

28
00:01:27,387 --> 00:01:29,089
SHE STORMED INTO ME
WHEN I WAS NERVOUS

29
00:01:29,155 --> 00:01:31,257
-But you made it so fun for me…
-Oh, my.

30
00:01:31,324 --> 00:01:34,561
…so I wondered if I should give you
my business card before I left.

31
00:01:34,627 --> 00:01:37,030
So you thought of her as you left?

32
00:01:37,097 --> 00:01:38,431
-I was thinking about it.
-And?

33
00:01:38,498 --> 00:01:40,867
But right after the shooting,
she said, "Good work,"

34
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:42,936
and stormed off immediately.

35
00:01:43,002 --> 00:01:44,904
-You aren't clingy.
-I'm not.

36
00:01:44,971 --> 00:01:47,941
I said, "Good work,"
and left like a professional.

37
00:01:48,007 --> 00:01:49,809
She's a pro.
A professional TV personality.

38
00:01:49,876 --> 00:01:52,479
Her professionality surprised me.

39
00:01:52,545 --> 00:01:54,681
So? Do you want my number today?

40
00:01:55,448 --> 00:01:57,250
THE CAMERAMAN IS CURIOUS TOO

41
00:01:57,317 --> 00:02:00,253
-I'll give you my business card.
-His business card.

42
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,423
Don't just leave the restaurant's number.
Give her your number.

43
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:06,326
-That happens with business cards.
-She offered her number.

44
00:02:06,392 --> 00:02:08,661
-It can't be just the business.
-It can't start with the city code 02.

45
00:02:08,728 --> 00:02:10,830
-It can't be just the 02 number.
-She needs a mobile 010 number.

46
00:02:10,897 --> 00:02:12,632
-I'll give you my number.
-Is it your number?

47
00:02:12,699 --> 00:02:14,234
-It's there.
-It's there.

48
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:16,736
-And one more chair is empty.
-Yes.

49
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:19,873
One more chair is empty.
Is it for a new special chef?

50
00:02:19,939 --> 00:02:21,908
-Yes.
-I wonder who it is.

51
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:26,079
When the chefs heard
this chef would be on the show,

52
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:30,116
there was one particular chef
who was in great shock.

53
00:02:30,183 --> 00:02:32,819
-Who was it?
-He flopped on the ground.

54
00:02:32,886 --> 00:02:36,689
-Chef Rok! Why were you so surprised?
-Goodness.

55
00:02:36,756 --> 00:02:39,392
Do you have a history
with the chef who'll come today?

56
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:40,994
-Yes, we do have a history.
-I see.

57
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:42,695
It's… Yes.

58
00:02:42,762 --> 00:02:44,597
-You can't leave in the middle.
-Oh, no.

59
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,266
Please stay vigilant.

60
00:02:46,332 --> 00:02:47,734
Let's invite her right away.

61
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:52,038
This chef flew in from Vienna, Austria.

62
00:02:52,105 --> 00:02:54,107
-That's so cool.
-This is amazing.

63
00:02:54,174 --> 00:02:56,809
We're very grateful
and happy to see this chef.

64
00:02:56,876 --> 00:02:57,877
Please come on out!

65
00:02:57,944 --> 00:03:00,180
Please come on out!

66
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:02,482
-Please come on out!
-Who will it be?

67
00:03:02,549 --> 00:03:05,418
She came all the way from Vienna, Austria.

68
00:03:05,485 --> 00:03:07,921
She came all the way from Vienna, Austria.

69
00:03:07,987 --> 00:03:09,589
Welcome to the show.

70
00:03:09,656 --> 00:03:10,857
-Hello!
-Yes, everyone.

71
00:03:10,924 --> 00:03:12,725
-Hello!
-She's here.

72
00:03:12,792 --> 00:03:14,594
<i>The queen chef of Vienna.</i>

73
00:03:14,661 --> 00:03:17,230
Please welcome Chef Kim Sohyi!

74
00:03:18,898 --> 00:03:22,902
<i>I'm very happy to be here.</i>

75
00:03:22,969 --> 00:03:24,537
<i>Thank you for inviting me.</i>

76
00:03:24,604 --> 00:03:26,673
-All right!
-Yes, please have a seat.

77
00:03:26,739 --> 00:03:28,775
-Welcome.
-Hello.

78
00:03:30,743 --> 00:03:32,111
Was that German?

79
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:35,982
If I talked like how I always would,
no one seemed to understand.

80
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:38,718
-No one understood?
-I thought some might understand German.

81
00:03:38,785 --> 00:03:41,287
-Yes, German.
-That's why I began with it.

82
00:03:41,354 --> 00:03:42,589
-Yes.
-People from Seoul go…

83
00:03:42,655 --> 00:03:44,157
THE FACE OF INCOMPREHENSIBILITY

84
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,758
-When they make that face…
-I see.

85
00:03:45,825 --> 00:03:47,460
…I know they don't understand.

86
00:03:47,527 --> 00:03:49,028
You were like that too.

87
00:03:50,330 --> 00:03:51,731
You were like that too.

88
00:03:51,798 --> 00:03:52,832
REELING

89
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:55,068
THEIR CHEMISTRY IS
STILL THE SAME

90
00:03:55,134 --> 00:03:57,637
-You did that too.
-You did.

91
00:03:57,704 --> 00:04:00,440
You two should
look each other in the eyes.

92
00:04:00,506 --> 00:04:02,609
-He's always like this.
-He is?

93
00:04:02,675 --> 00:04:04,244
-He's always like that?
-This kid.

94
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:06,412
Hasn't it been a while
since you two have met?

95
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:08,214
-I thought so.
-Hasn't it been a while?

96
00:04:08,281 --> 00:04:09,983
-It's been a while, right?
-Yes.

97
00:04:10,049 --> 00:04:11,584
He hasn't changed a bit. Even then…

98
00:04:12,485 --> 00:04:15,822
He was like that even back then?

99
00:04:15,888 --> 00:04:17,657
Even back then?

100
00:04:18,224 --> 00:04:20,493
-And he did that for over a decade?
-His eyes.

101
00:04:21,861 --> 00:04:23,863
It means he's unchanging.

102
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:25,531
Are you happy to see her, though?

103
00:04:25,598 --> 00:04:27,367
-I am.
-I see.

104
00:04:27,433 --> 00:04:30,236
He finally looked me in the eyes.
He wouldn't do that.

105
00:04:30,303 --> 00:04:32,472
Can you give her a hug?

106
00:04:32,538 --> 00:04:35,475
Let's see the contestant
giving a hug to the judge.

107
00:04:35,541 --> 00:04:37,677
-Yes, let's see it.
-It's a reunion.

108
00:04:37,744 --> 00:04:39,379
It's been a while.

109
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:42,048
-Give her a hug from the back.
-It's been a while.

110
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:43,650
They've reunited after 12 years.

111
00:04:43,716 --> 00:04:46,352
Now, come. It's been so long.

112
00:04:47,086 --> 00:04:48,521
IT'S GREAT TO SEE YOU!

113
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:52,225
-It's been so long.
-All right!

114
00:04:54,193 --> 00:04:56,462
AWKWARD

115
00:04:57,530 --> 00:04:59,065
He's in trouble.

116
00:04:59,132 --> 00:05:00,133
-He's in trouble.
-Will he…

117
00:05:00,199 --> 00:05:02,568
-Will he be able to cook today?
-He's in trouble. Right?

118
00:05:02,635 --> 00:05:05,405
Chef Sohyi, was there a special reason
you visited us here?

119
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:08,541
I'm on the older side now.

120
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:11,644
So I wanted to try working
with the younger generation.

121
00:05:11,711 --> 00:05:15,448
I wondered if I'd also feel youthful
if I work with these younger ones.

122
00:05:15,515 --> 00:05:19,352
To younger chefs like me and Chef Nam-no,

123
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:22,055
she was someone we looked up to.

124
00:05:22,121 --> 00:05:26,225
It'll be the most proper to call her
the most legendary of all legends.

125
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:27,593
-That's huge.
-Thank you.

126
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,862
-Yes, she's a judge.
-Of course.

127
00:05:29,929 --> 00:05:32,999
-She's not usually a competitor.
-You're right.

128
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:34,967
Chef Sohyi, I heard you requested

129
00:05:35,034 --> 00:05:37,103
-an interpreter to our production crew.
-An interpreter?

130
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:38,971
-People don't understand me.
-They don't?

131
00:05:39,038 --> 00:05:42,608
-People from Seoul don't understand.
-People from Seoul.

132
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:45,812
So we invited someone
who's fluent in the Busan dialect,

133
00:05:45,878 --> 00:05:50,316
-who is it?
-a native of Busan as an interpreter.

134
00:05:50,383 --> 00:05:54,420
These guests are
literally popular worldwide.

135
00:05:54,487 --> 00:05:56,656
Please welcome

136
00:05:56,723 --> 00:05:58,791
-today's fridge owners!
-Come on out!

137
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:00,360
All right!

138
00:06:00,426 --> 00:06:01,994
They're the fridge owners today.

139
00:06:02,061 --> 00:06:04,697
-Please welcome…
-Who could they be?

140
00:06:04,764 --> 00:06:06,699
…today's fridge owners!

141
00:06:06,766 --> 00:06:09,235
-Please welcome…
-Who could they be?

142
00:06:09,302 --> 00:06:11,504
…today's fridge owners!

143
00:06:12,271 --> 00:06:16,075
j-hope of BTS and Heo Sung-tae!

144
00:06:17,276 --> 00:06:19,412
<i>A group that rewrote the history of K-pop.</i>

145
00:06:19,479 --> 00:06:22,448
<i>The first K-pop group to reach</i>
<i>first place in the Billboard charts.</i>

146
00:06:22,515 --> 00:06:26,452
<i>The first Korean song to reach</i>
<i>first place in the Billboard charts.</i>

147
00:06:26,519 --> 00:06:29,188
<i>They were the first group</i>
<i>after The Beatles</i>

148
00:06:29,255 --> 00:06:33,526
<i>to put six first-place songs</i>
<i>on the Hot 100 Chart in the Billboards.</i>

149
00:06:33,593 --> 00:06:36,062
<i>That's right.</i>
<i>From BTS, a world-renowned boy band,</i>

150
00:06:36,129 --> 00:06:38,731
please welcome j-hope!

151
00:06:40,967 --> 00:06:42,568
All right!

152
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,371
The viewers are very excited about this.

153
00:06:45,438 --> 00:06:46,939
Please greet them into the camera.

154
00:06:47,006 --> 00:06:49,942
Hello, I'm j-hope of BTS.

155
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:51,978
I've returned
after my mandatory military service.

156
00:06:53,112 --> 00:06:55,314
IT'S GREAT TO HAVE YOU HERE

157
00:06:55,381 --> 00:06:58,851
-He became more energetic and stylish.
-He did.

158
00:06:58,918 --> 00:07:00,653
It's great to see you.

159
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:03,589
-It's been so long. And…
-Yes, really.

160
00:07:03,656 --> 00:07:06,692
This guy here looks kind of nervous.

161
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:08,361
He's usually not like this.

162
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:11,497
I think he has
a similar vibe to Chef Kang-rok.

163
00:07:11,564 --> 00:07:15,501
Yes, look at the way he's sitting.
His shoulders look hunched.

164
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:16,769
Their postures are similar too.

165
00:07:16,836 --> 00:07:21,707
-I'll give them more energy.
-Wait, is it because of Chef Sohyi?

166
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:24,076
-Let me introduce him to you.
-Yes, a formal introduction.

167
00:07:24,143 --> 00:07:26,045
If you want to go, go first!

168
00:07:26,612 --> 00:07:28,648
<i>A man who became known</i>

169
00:07:28,714 --> 00:07:31,651
<i>as the bad guy after playing</i>
<i>the biggest villain of</i> Squid Game!

170
00:07:31,717 --> 00:07:33,085
Please welcome actor Heo Sung-tae!

171
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:35,021
Heo Sung-tae!

172
00:07:37,757 --> 00:07:38,891
Hello, I'm Heo Sung-tae, an actor.

173
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:41,861
You should look at our viewers here.

174
00:07:41,928 --> 00:07:43,496
Hello, I'm Heo Sung-tae, an actor.

175
00:07:43,563 --> 00:07:46,299
Welcome to the show.

176
00:07:46,365 --> 00:07:48,434
Why do you look so…

177
00:07:48,501 --> 00:07:50,770
-Are they brothers?
-They're the same.

178
00:07:50,837 --> 00:07:52,638
-They could be brothers.
-Yes.

179
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:57,176
I was surprised back there
by how shy he was.

180
00:07:57,243 --> 00:08:00,079
You're now watching
Sung-tae's unfamiliar side.

181
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:05,651
First, j-hope is here at <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

182
00:08:05,718 --> 00:08:08,554
I wanted to know
if you had a special reason.

183
00:08:08,621 --> 00:08:12,725
-Well, it's one of my favorite programs.
-I see.

184
00:08:12,792 --> 00:08:15,962
I also released a new single

185
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:18,631
-and have a concert coming up too.
-Is that so?

186
00:08:18,698 --> 00:08:21,334
I wanted to let many people know

187
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,970
and hoped they'd be interested.

188
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:28,274
So honestly speaking, you came for PR.

189
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:31,410
You could've just said
he came for many reasons.

190
00:08:31,477 --> 00:08:32,945
But what can be better than this?

191
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:36,716
-I get to eat good food and promote.
-Isn't it great?

192
00:08:36,782 --> 00:08:38,651
-Yes.
-And you get to meet the viewers.

193
00:08:38,718 --> 00:08:40,853
-Yes.
-It's wonderful.

194
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:43,589
Sung-tae, did you also come
to promote something?

195
00:08:43,656 --> 00:08:47,927
I made a request to be here
because it was my mom's favorite show.

196
00:08:47,994 --> 00:08:50,863
-He made a request.
-He requested it first.

197
00:08:50,930 --> 00:08:52,465
Did your mother make the request?

198
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:53,766
We rarely hear a fridge owner

199
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,701
-use the word "request."
-Requested.

200
00:08:55,768 --> 00:08:57,203
Did you take the number stub?

201
00:08:57,270 --> 00:08:58,971
No, I saw the ad

202
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:01,107
-that said the show was restarting.
-The ad?

203
00:09:01,173 --> 00:09:03,376
Then I told my manager

204
00:09:03,442 --> 00:09:04,710
I really wanted to do it.

205
00:09:06,178 --> 00:09:07,313
Without doing any promotions?

206
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,015
Well, I do have something.

207
00:09:09,081 --> 00:09:10,816
-You do?
-You have something to promote?

208
00:09:10,883 --> 00:09:15,021
I'll be appearing
in a JTBC drama called <i>Good Boy</i>.

209
00:09:15,087 --> 00:09:16,155
<i>Good Boy.</i>

210
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:18,457
We'll begin airing at the end of May.

211
00:09:18,524 --> 00:09:21,561
-Sung-tae, what are you looking at?
-That.

212
00:09:21,627 --> 00:09:23,362
-That place?
-This area.

213
00:09:23,429 --> 00:09:26,866
A JTBC drama called <i>Good Boy</i>
will go on air in May.

214
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:29,502
-At the end of May.
-The end of May?

215
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:31,804
The timing was impeccable.

216
00:09:31,871 --> 00:09:33,739
-I see.
-That sounds great.

217
00:09:33,806 --> 00:09:36,309
And I also like to cook.

218
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:39,045
-Yes.
-I see.

219
00:09:40,012 --> 00:09:43,716
-They're so similar.
-But after you came here, you realized

220
00:09:43,783 --> 00:09:46,719
-you'd be here with j-hope of BTS.
-Right.

221
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:53,693
We had a chef here
whom j-hope wanted to meet in person.

222
00:09:54,860 --> 00:09:57,930
-He wanted to nitpick over something.
-Nitpick?

223
00:09:57,997 --> 00:10:00,232
Who did you want to meet in person?

224
00:10:00,299 --> 00:10:02,001
-I wouldn't say I wanted to nitpick.
-Then?

225
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:04,704
-Look at his eyes.
-Who is it?

226
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:05,905
-Who?
-Someone's looking away.

227
00:10:05,972 --> 00:10:07,707
Someone's avoiding his eyes,
dropping his head.

228
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:08,841
-What did you do?
-Who is it?

229
00:10:08,908 --> 00:10:11,544
I received a lot of criticism.

230
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,179
-Are you turning yourself in?
-Why?

231
00:10:13,245 --> 00:10:16,983
The show he was on
became really huge, right?

232
00:10:17,049 --> 00:10:21,220
While I was watching,
I was captured by Chef Nam-no's charisma.

233
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:22,955
He captured you with this.

234
00:10:23,022 --> 00:10:25,725
So I uploaded a post about him
on my social media account.

235
00:10:26,726 --> 00:10:28,260
-On your account?
-Yes.

236
00:10:28,327 --> 00:10:30,496
He has so many followers!

237
00:10:30,563 --> 00:10:32,732
-Okay, and?
-Yes, and? Isn't that a good thing?

238
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:34,634
-It's a great thing.
-It must be great.

239
00:10:35,568 --> 00:10:37,803
On this other show…

240
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:39,939
-Yes, on another show?
-On another show?

241
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:43,376
He went on another show and said
he knew of BTS.

242
00:10:43,442 --> 00:10:45,611
And of course, I understand.

243
00:10:45,678 --> 00:10:47,513
But he said he didn't know j-hope.

244
00:10:48,714 --> 00:10:51,250
-You said that on TV?
-Are you crazy?

245
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:53,152
I had to come here to promote myself.

246
00:10:53,219 --> 00:10:55,554
-I wanted him to know who j-hope was.
-This is bad.

247
00:10:55,621 --> 00:10:58,190
-My goodness.
-How can he say that?

248
00:10:58,257 --> 00:11:02,762
He wanted to help Chef Nam-no find out
who j-hope was.

249
00:11:02,828 --> 00:11:06,732
-My gosh.
-So that was the full story.

250
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:09,035
-Let's hear from Chef Nam-no too.
-Let's hear it.

251
00:11:09,101 --> 00:11:10,603
It could happen.

252
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,138
Honestly speaking,

253
00:11:12,204 --> 00:11:14,407
-I don't have a TV at home.
-I see.

254
00:11:14,473 --> 00:11:16,208
I don't have a TV at home.

255
00:11:16,275 --> 00:11:19,045
I just have a washing machine
and a bed to sleep on.

256
00:11:19,111 --> 00:11:21,580
-But you have your phone.
-You have your phone.

257
00:11:21,647 --> 00:11:24,150
Can you please help me out this once?

258
00:11:24,717 --> 00:11:26,118
YOU CAN SENSE HIS SINCERITY

259
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:27,853
Yes, this can become scandalous.

260
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,822
-Okay.
-He's serious about this.

261
00:11:29,889 --> 00:11:31,824
Let's hear his serious explanation.

262
00:11:31,891 --> 00:11:34,160
-That's just an excuse.
-Anyway, hey.

263
00:11:34,226 --> 00:11:36,529
You'd know who j-hope is
if you had a fan at home.

264
00:11:36,595 --> 00:11:38,731
-You're killing him.
-Stop that.

265
00:11:38,798 --> 00:11:41,400
-Will you end him right here?
-Just let him live.

266
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:44,937
j-hope is now here where you are, Nam-no.

267
00:11:45,004 --> 00:11:47,206
-It's great.
-He wanted to taste

268
00:11:47,273 --> 00:11:49,475
-the dish Chef Nam-no made.
-Yes, right.

269
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,477
I'm having a lot of fun now.

270
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:53,212
-How is he in person?
-I feel like

271
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:56,515
-I've become a lucky fan.
-A lucky fan.

272
00:11:56,582 --> 00:11:58,250
-All right!
-Look at him.

273
00:11:59,752 --> 00:12:03,022
But I loved all chefs
who appeared on that show.

274
00:12:03,089 --> 00:12:04,857
I enjoyed it a lot.

275
00:12:04,924 --> 00:12:08,127
Sung-tae, I also heard
you had a chef you wanted to meet.

276
00:12:08,994 --> 00:12:10,830
-Her.
-She was right next to you.

277
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:11,964
I see.

278
00:12:12,031 --> 00:12:13,833
-That was why he was nervous.
-I guess so.

279
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:14,900
Have you known about Chef Sohyi?

280
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:17,136
Yes, she's so charismatic.

281
00:12:17,203 --> 00:12:19,705
I wanted to eat something
that was charismatic.

282
00:12:19,772 --> 00:12:23,242
-A charismatic dish.
-He wants to eat something charismatic.

283
00:12:23,309 --> 00:12:27,279
We actually let you sit
next to Chef Sohyi on purpose.

284
00:12:27,346 --> 00:12:30,483
-Sung-tae is from Busan.
-That's great.

285
00:12:30,549 --> 00:12:33,719
-So can you be her interpreter today?
-Yes.

286
00:12:33,786 --> 00:12:36,288
How will he interpret me
if he can't even speak?

287
00:12:36,856 --> 00:12:39,225
FACT BOMBING(?)

288
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:42,027
He's too shy even to speak,
so you don't think he can do it?

289
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:43,796
Did you just understand?

290
00:12:43,863 --> 00:12:44,864
-Yes.
-I can.

291
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:46,966
-"He can't even speak."
-He can't do it if he's too shy to speak.

292
00:12:47,032 --> 00:12:49,034
Can you two start talking in that dialect?

293
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:51,604
-If you have any questions, ask her.
-Where are you from?

294
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:53,973
-Beomil-dong.
-Beomil-dong? I'm from Yeongju-dong.

295
00:12:54,039 --> 00:12:55,875
-Yeongju-dong? I see.
-Yes.

296
00:12:55,941 --> 00:12:56,942
Okay.

297
00:12:59,745 --> 00:13:02,715
-It seems like he's playing a shy role.
-It's as if he's acting.

298
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:06,519
I'll do my best to interpret her
as we continue.

299
00:13:06,585 --> 00:13:11,423
j-hope recently put on
a wonderful show in Paris, France.

300
00:13:11,490 --> 00:13:15,060
French President Macron's wife

301
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:17,763
<i>invited him there herself</i>

302
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:19,665
to perform the opening act.

303
00:13:19,732 --> 00:13:21,233
The tickets were sold out in ten minutes.

304
00:13:22,334 --> 00:13:26,372
-Gosh. That's crazy.
-Many people came to see j-hope.

305
00:13:26,438 --> 00:13:30,776
I believe the venue held
between 30,000 to 40,000 people.

306
00:13:30,843 --> 00:13:32,011
He boosted our national prestige.

307
00:13:32,077 --> 00:13:34,680
It was my first performance
after my military discharge,

308
00:13:34,747 --> 00:13:37,449
-so I was rather nervous.
-I understand.

309
00:13:37,516 --> 00:13:40,085
But unlike how you were nervous,
the crowd sang along in Korean.

310
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:43,823
-Yes, the crowd sang along in Korean.
-Yes, they sang along.

311
00:13:43,889 --> 00:13:46,492
Everyone said sorry to their moms.

312
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:48,928
Yes, everyone said sorry to their moms.

313
00:13:48,994 --> 00:13:51,597
They all shouted, "I'm sorry, Mom!"
I was surprised too.

314
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:52,731
That's amazing.

315
00:13:52,798 --> 00:13:53,833
-Isn't it?
-It is.

316
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:55,267
"That's amazing."

317
00:13:55,935 --> 00:13:57,603
INTERPRETING HER DIALECT
INTO A DIALECT

318
00:13:57,670 --> 00:14:00,606
You can share your thoughts too.

319
00:14:00,673 --> 00:14:02,374
-He is so cool.
-Wasn't he?

320
00:14:04,109 --> 00:14:05,211
Yes.

321
00:14:05,277 --> 00:14:06,645
It seemed like

322
00:14:06,712 --> 00:14:13,118
other world-renowned stars were
a part of this concert.

323
00:14:13,185 --> 00:14:14,854
-Was Sung-tae there?
-Hey.

324
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,789
-No? He wasn't there.
-Sung-tae?

325
00:14:18,123 --> 00:14:21,760
It was someone who was
in the same production, Lee Jung-jae.

326
00:14:23,229 --> 00:14:25,297
I see. Jung-jae was there?

327
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:26,432
Did you two take pictures?

328
00:14:26,498 --> 00:14:29,335
Yes, we did.

329
00:14:29,401 --> 00:14:30,903
I was so surprised.

330
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:34,974
The letters on his camera app were

331
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:38,143
-really big.
-The font?

332
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:41,981
-The font was big.
-He became farsighted with age.

333
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:45,651
The font wasn't the size I was used to.

334
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,686
I told him about that,

335
00:14:47,753 --> 00:14:51,557
-<i>and he laughed it off like it was funny.</i>
-<i>I thought he'd be chill.</i>

336
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:53,459
He said, "I can't really see now."

337
00:14:53,525 --> 00:14:54,827
-I can definitely connect.
-That was hilarious.

338
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:55,961
I can connect, Jung-jae.

339
00:14:56,028 --> 00:14:57,162
Why? How?

340
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:59,498
-We were born in the Year of the Mouse.
-You're both mice.

341
00:14:59,565 --> 00:15:01,533
My friend, Hyun-suk, me,

342
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:04,470
-Kyun, and Jung-jae are the same age.
-Kyun?

343
00:15:04,536 --> 00:15:07,306
-You're all the same age.
-I have to look at it like this.

344
00:15:07,373 --> 00:15:09,008
-Farsightedness due to age.
-Yes.

345
00:15:09,074 --> 00:15:11,310
If you ever meet Jung-jae
or talk to him on the phone,

346
00:15:11,377 --> 00:15:16,081
-tell him that Hyun-suk makes a mean dish.
-All right.

347
00:15:16,148 --> 00:15:19,618
-The mice can get together.
-We should all get together.

348
00:15:19,685 --> 00:15:22,755
I have a feeling
your solo release will be amazing.

349
00:15:22,821 --> 00:15:25,391
It's the first time

350
00:15:25,457 --> 00:15:26,959
I'm singing a love song.

351
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:28,227
-The first love song?
-Yes.

352
00:15:28,294 --> 00:15:30,129
A love song.

353
00:15:30,195 --> 00:15:31,397
I feel embarrassed.

354
00:15:31,463 --> 00:15:33,899
-Will you do a solo world tour?
-Yes.

355
00:15:33,966 --> 00:15:35,067
Where are you going?

356
00:15:35,134 --> 00:15:38,570
I'm going to 15 different cities.

357
00:15:38,637 --> 00:15:41,407
I'll begin in North America.

358
00:15:41,473 --> 00:15:44,143
-After America, I'll go to South America.
-America. South America.

359
00:15:44,209 --> 00:15:46,745
Then I'll return to Asia

360
00:15:46,812 --> 00:15:50,082
and stop by Japan, Singapore,
Taiwan, and more.

361
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:53,018
-Are you coming to Vienna too?
-Sorry?

362
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:55,487
-Austria.
-"Are you coming to Vienna too?"

363
00:15:55,554 --> 00:15:56,989
HEO SUNG-TAE,
THE DIALECT INTERPRETER

364
00:15:57,056 --> 00:15:59,458
-The interpreter.
-He stepped in for a moment.

365
00:15:59,525 --> 00:16:01,527
Sung-tae gave an exact translation.

366
00:16:01,593 --> 00:16:04,296
-Will you come to Vienna?
-There was a bit of delay.

367
00:16:04,363 --> 00:16:06,665
Yes, I don't feel frustrated anymore.

368
00:16:06,732 --> 00:16:08,467
"I don't feel frustrated anymore."

369
00:16:08,534 --> 00:16:11,136
You don't have to interpret
what we can understand, though.

370
00:16:11,203 --> 00:16:13,172
-Yes, okay.
-Okay.

371
00:16:13,238 --> 00:16:15,774
Sadly, I won't be visiting Vienna.

372
00:16:15,841 --> 00:16:17,943
-You won't come to Vienna?
-"You won't come to Vienna?"

373
00:16:18,877 --> 00:16:21,714
HE CAN'T HELP BUT DO HIS JOB

374
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:25,017
He's repeating after me like an echo.

375
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:31,457
It hasn't been long
since j-hope was discharged from the army.

376
00:16:31,523 --> 00:16:33,525
He's fresh out of the army.

377
00:16:33,592 --> 00:16:36,562
I wonder what it was like
for a world-renowned star to serve there.

378
00:16:36,628 --> 00:16:37,763
-What was it like?
-Right?

379
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:42,067
I served
in the Baekho Recruit Training Center

380
00:16:42,134 --> 00:16:45,270
-as a drill sergeant.
-You were a drill sergeant?

381
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:47,940
I see. Did you wear a red cap?

382
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:50,275
-And the drill sergeant insignia.
-The insignia.

383
00:16:50,342 --> 00:16:51,777
It kind of makes you proud.

384
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:55,047
That little patch makes you feel…

385
00:16:55,114 --> 00:16:57,049
FEELING PROUD

386
00:16:57,116 --> 00:16:59,752
Drill sergeants have that pride.

387
00:16:59,818 --> 00:17:02,154
-He received lots of awards there.
-He did?

388
00:17:02,221 --> 00:17:05,057
<i>He was an outstanding drill sergeant</i>
<i>and an excellent soldier.</i>

389
00:17:05,124 --> 00:17:06,125
<i>An excellent squad commander.</i>

390
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:09,194
He even received an award
during one of the contests.

391
00:17:09,261 --> 00:17:10,863
You participated in everything.

392
00:17:11,563 --> 00:17:12,798
-He did.
-Yes.

393
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:15,601
-You should've stayed in there.
-Seriously.

394
00:17:15,667 --> 00:17:18,437
His fans were worried he might do that.

395
00:17:18,504 --> 00:17:21,407
-They were worried he'd stay.
-He must've been in his element.

396
00:17:21,473 --> 00:17:27,012
I was trained
in the same recruit training center

397
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:29,982
as the one I was appointed to.

398
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:33,719
And when I had the food there,
it was so delicious.

399
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:35,187
You must've liked it.

400
00:17:35,254 --> 00:17:37,022
It tastes even better after you train.

401
00:17:37,089 --> 00:17:40,993
They didn't serve something ordinary
like you'd expect at the army.

402
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,429
They even served <i>mala tteokbokki</i>.

403
00:17:43,495 --> 00:17:45,097
-In the army?
-They're up with the trend.

404
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:47,499
-Yes, it was trendy.
-Things have changed.

405
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:48,801
I was like, "Hey, not bad."

406
00:17:48,867 --> 00:17:52,738
I thought, "My year and a half here
shouldn't be that bad."

407
00:17:52,805 --> 00:17:54,873
You felt like you'd be content?

408
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:56,008
That was a huge factor.

409
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:58,811
It looks like he's a serious foodie.

410
00:17:58,877 --> 00:18:03,015
I began to want to eat something delicious
if I'm going to eat something.

411
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:05,984
I became more like that
after my military service.

412
00:18:06,051 --> 00:18:07,986
So you're still in that attitude.

413
00:18:08,053 --> 00:18:12,191
Now, we're about to show you
j-hope's fridge very soon.

414
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:14,626
Before we do that,
let's find out his order

415
00:18:14,693 --> 00:18:17,729
and decide on the contenders.

416
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:21,100
Show us his orders!

417
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:22,167
Skate is…

418
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:23,502
ON FIRE

419
00:18:23,569 --> 00:18:26,338
FIRE

420
00:18:26,405 --> 00:18:30,509
A SURPRISE LIVE PERFORMANCE
FOR THE WORLD-RENOWNED J-HOPE

421
00:18:30,576 --> 00:18:33,312
"Skate is on fire." Do you enjoy skate?

422
00:18:33,378 --> 00:18:34,880
-I think he's in shock.
-I am

423
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:37,316
-originally from Gwangju.
-I see.

424
00:18:37,883 --> 00:18:40,285
When we'd hold ancestral rites as a child,

425
00:18:40,352 --> 00:18:42,988
-we often served it on the table.
-You must be familiar with it.

426
00:18:43,055 --> 00:18:44,723
So since when I was that young,

427
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:48,460
-I naturally began to eat it.
-It's not easy to develop a taste for it.

428
00:18:48,527 --> 00:18:51,430
I just dip uncooked skate
in chogochujang to this day.

429
00:18:51,497 --> 00:18:54,900
I also heard
it was good for bones and cartilages.

430
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:58,470
I began to get interested in such things
ever since I got discharged.

431
00:18:58,537 --> 00:19:01,607
-It's good for you too.
-Yes, I thought I should have some

432
00:19:01,673 --> 00:19:05,777
and got interested in
what aged fish tasted like.

433
00:19:06,512 --> 00:19:08,113
I love how he titled the order.

434
00:19:08,180 --> 00:19:11,517
When you eat fermented skate,
it sets your nose on fire.

435
00:19:11,583 --> 00:19:15,154
-Fire!
-Fire!

436
00:19:15,721 --> 00:19:17,122
Fire!

437
00:19:17,189 --> 00:19:19,391
Let's find out his next order.

438
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:21,693
Dessert…

439
00:19:22,261 --> 00:19:26,532
WHY DO YOU SHAKE UP MY HEART?

440
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:30,135
Welcome.
It's your first time hearing BTS, right?

441
00:19:32,371 --> 00:19:34,506
It sounds like you want dessert.

442
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:38,310
I have a serious sweet tooth,
so really love dessert.

443
00:19:38,377 --> 00:19:39,878
It's a great end to a meal.

444
00:19:39,945 --> 00:19:42,814
I could remember a good meal
when I had a good dessert.

445
00:19:42,881 --> 00:19:43,982
-Feeling good as you leave.
-Yes.

446
00:19:44,049 --> 00:19:45,450
But that's not the only reason.

447
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:47,219
When I went abroad,

448
00:19:47,286 --> 00:19:49,288
the hotels would give
complimentary snacks,

449
00:19:49,354 --> 00:19:51,523
including their local sweets.

450
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:52,791
When I go back to Korea,

451
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:55,327
it's a shame to leave the snacks there.

452
00:19:55,394 --> 00:19:57,930
So I usually pack up
the things I can take.

453
00:19:57,996 --> 00:20:00,165
I actually do that too.

454
00:20:00,232 --> 00:20:03,335
-That's how much I like desserts.
-You must like it.

455
00:20:03,402 --> 00:20:07,039
-I see.
-He's frugal when it comes to desserts.

456
00:20:07,105 --> 00:20:10,776
Tiramisu has to be my favorite, though.

457
00:20:10,842 --> 00:20:12,177
-I see.
-Tiramisu.

458
00:20:12,244 --> 00:20:13,445
These are good tips.

459
00:20:13,512 --> 00:20:16,682
-He likes tiramisu.
-I see.

460
00:20:16,748 --> 00:20:18,784
-One of the orders involve skate.
-Yes.

461
00:20:18,850 --> 00:20:21,787
<i>It was one of the themes</i>
<i>for</i> Culinary Chef Wars <i>too</i>.

462
00:20:21,853 --> 00:20:22,921
-<i>Chef Sung-jun.</i>
-<i>Chef Sung-jun did that.</i>

463
00:20:22,988 --> 00:20:25,991
-I did it as the skate expert.
-You did that.

464
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:27,993
I'd feel confident
if I took up that theme.

465
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,294
Yes, right.

466
00:20:29,361 --> 00:20:31,496
-I'm kind of intrigued.
-Are you thinking about it?

467
00:20:31,563 --> 00:20:33,298
-You're good with both.
-I want to do both.

468
00:20:33,365 --> 00:20:34,366
Do the skate once again.

469
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:37,236
Skate is a great ingredient,

470
00:20:37,302 --> 00:20:38,937
so I'll let other chefs work with it.

471
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:42,107
I'll go for the dessert.

472
00:20:42,841 --> 00:20:45,344
-I see.
-It must be hard to work with skate.

473
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:46,411
I guess it's not easy.

474
00:20:46,478 --> 00:20:51,283
-I'll go for the dessert.
-Dessert.

475
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,451
He avoids the skate.

476
00:20:52,517 --> 00:20:55,520
Won-young also gave him a heart
after she had his dessert.

477
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:57,055
She did.

478
00:20:57,122 --> 00:20:58,724
WON-YOUNG GAVE HEARTS
AFTER EATING HIS DESSERT

479
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:01,793
Tomorrow is my birthday.

480
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:04,796
-Is that so?
-What are the chances?

481
00:21:04,863 --> 00:21:06,565
HAPPENS TO BE HOBI'S BIRTHDAY

482
00:21:06,632 --> 00:21:11,503
-This dessert may be very significant.
-I guess so.

483
00:21:11,570 --> 00:21:14,539
Everyone is avoiding the skate right now.

484
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:17,075
Chef Nam-no, if you don't go for it,

485
00:21:17,142 --> 00:21:19,511
you won't find a chance to cook for him.

486
00:21:19,578 --> 00:21:21,313
-I'll go for it.
-He will!

487
00:21:22,347 --> 00:21:25,117
-Nam-no takes the skate.
-That's so cool.

488
00:21:25,183 --> 00:21:26,685
It'll be so meaningful.

489
00:21:26,752 --> 00:21:28,353
Right? Yes.

490
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:29,888
Skate sounds delicious.

491
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:31,390
Be quiet.

492
00:21:32,057 --> 00:21:34,159
Now, hey, Poong.

493
00:21:34,226 --> 00:21:35,460
-Yes?
-Poong?

494
00:21:35,527 --> 00:21:38,063
-Skate?
-I'll work with skate too.

495
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,131
Are you sure?

496
00:21:39,197 --> 00:21:40,932
I really like skate too.

497
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,769
I really love to eat skate too.

498
00:21:43,835 --> 00:21:45,470
-I look forward to this.
-All right, then.

499
00:21:45,537 --> 00:21:49,308
Nam-no and Poong will begin their round.

500
00:21:49,374 --> 00:21:51,209
THE CONTENDERS ARE DECIDED
FOR J-HOPE'S FRIDGE

501
00:21:51,276 --> 00:21:55,914
It's time to find out
what the world-renowned j-hope keeps

502
00:21:55,981 --> 00:21:58,016
inside his fridge.

503
00:21:58,083 --> 00:22:00,018
This isn't from your dorm, right?

504
00:22:00,085 --> 00:22:01,520
-You've moved out.
-Yes.

505
00:22:01,586 --> 00:22:02,721
Has it been a while?

506
00:22:02,788 --> 00:22:06,491
I moved out of the dorm around 2018.

507
00:22:06,558 --> 00:22:08,927
That was much later than I thought.

508
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:11,129
Yes, we all lived in the dorm for a while.

509
00:22:11,196 --> 00:22:13,532
-He's a world-renowned star…
-Right.

510
00:22:13,598 --> 00:22:17,135
…so there may be ingredients
we haven't seen before.

511
00:22:17,202 --> 00:22:20,706
But I really don't have much in my fridge.

512
00:22:20,772 --> 00:22:23,475
-Food delivery is huge now, so…
-Right.

513
00:22:23,542 --> 00:22:25,477
-It happens when you live alone.
-Yes.

514
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:30,882
What kind of ingredients
does j-hope keep in his fridge?

515
00:22:30,949 --> 00:22:32,651
-All right.
-You have great skin.

516
00:22:33,952 --> 00:22:37,422
-Your skin looks great. I am.
-She's different from Jung-hwan.

517
00:22:37,489 --> 00:22:40,659
-Why is your skin so smooth? Be careful.
-Get away from me.

518
00:22:40,726 --> 00:22:43,395
I present j-hope's fridge!

519
00:22:43,462 --> 00:22:44,830
Here it is!

520
00:22:49,801 --> 00:22:50,802
J-HOPE'S FRIDGE LOOKS NEAT

521
00:22:50,869 --> 00:22:52,571
-It looks neat.
-Yes.

522
00:22:52,637 --> 00:22:54,272
-It's so neat.
-It is.

523
00:22:55,207 --> 00:22:56,208
The first shelf.

524
00:22:56,274 --> 00:22:58,710
-Look how these are lined up.
-It looks so neat.

525
00:22:58,777 --> 00:23:02,881
I'm the type who enjoys carbonated water

526
00:23:02,948 --> 00:23:04,850
instead of regular water.

527
00:23:04,916 --> 00:23:09,421
I need carbonated water
whenever I eat my meals.

528
00:23:09,488 --> 00:23:12,324
I see some beverages here,

529
00:23:12,391 --> 00:23:14,092
as well as coffee.

530
00:23:14,159 --> 00:23:15,794
There are some side dishes.

531
00:23:15,861 --> 00:23:17,429
How do you get the side dishes?

532
00:23:17,496 --> 00:23:19,898
My mother made those.

533
00:23:19,965 --> 00:23:22,401
At times, I get sick of eating

534
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:24,636
-just delivery food.
-You do.

535
00:23:24,703 --> 00:23:28,006
There are days when you crave
a home-cooked meal.

536
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:29,975
-These are deodeok.
-Deodeok.

537
00:23:30,041 --> 00:23:32,611
I like seasoned deodeok.

538
00:23:32,677 --> 00:23:33,845
Seasoned perilla leaves.

539
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:36,281
-My mouth is watering.
-Mine too.

540
00:23:36,348 --> 00:23:39,418
It's been a while
since I've had Korean food.

541
00:23:39,484 --> 00:23:40,619
I'm sure.

542
00:23:40,685 --> 00:23:41,920
Did your mother make this too?

543
00:23:41,987 --> 00:23:43,422
-It's kimchi.
-Kimchi.

544
00:23:43,488 --> 00:23:45,457
-Kimchi! My kimchi!
-"My kimchi."

545
00:23:45,524 --> 00:23:46,625
It's j-hope's kimchi.

546
00:23:46,691 --> 00:23:48,293
-No, my kimchi.
-She's craving some.

547
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:49,594
Would you like to taste this?

548
00:23:49,661 --> 00:23:50,896
-May I?
-Go ahead.

549
00:23:50,962 --> 00:23:53,565
-I'm from the southern area…
-The southern area.

550
00:23:53,632 --> 00:23:56,935
…so most of the side dishes
may be a bit too strong.

551
00:23:57,602 --> 00:23:58,837
Is it good?

552
00:23:58,904 --> 00:24:00,405
It's made by his mother.

553
00:24:00,472 --> 00:24:03,475
-Is it good?
-It's quite salty,

554
00:24:03,542 --> 00:24:05,777
and it was ripened perfectly.

555
00:24:05,844 --> 00:24:07,446
You must like Korean cuisine.

556
00:24:07,512 --> 00:24:09,915
It's my favorite type of food.

557
00:24:09,981 --> 00:24:12,451
What about
when you perform in America or Europe?

558
00:24:12,517 --> 00:24:16,855
When I go to another country,
I try to eat the food from there.

559
00:24:17,489 --> 00:24:20,592
I really like mango rice.

560
00:24:20,659 --> 00:24:23,261
-Mango rice. Is it good?
-It's really good.

561
00:24:23,328 --> 00:24:26,298
Do some of the members have a tough time
because they love

562
00:24:26,364 --> 00:24:27,432
-Korean food so much?
-Yes.

563
00:24:27,499 --> 00:24:29,468
-Yes? Who prefers Korean food?
-Yes.

564
00:24:29,534 --> 00:24:32,637
-RM prefers Korean cuisine…
-RM.

565
00:24:32,704 --> 00:24:34,539
…as well as V.

566
00:24:34,606 --> 00:24:37,809
-Jimin is what we call a child's appetite.
-A child's appetite.

567
00:24:37,876 --> 00:24:40,011
-I see.
-He likes pork cutlets.

568
00:24:40,078 --> 00:24:42,481
-Nothing with strong spice.
-Yes, that's right.

569
00:24:42,547 --> 00:24:43,615
Like a child's appetite.

570
00:24:43,682 --> 00:24:47,152
I'm finally seeing some main ingredients.

571
00:24:47,219 --> 00:24:49,454
I think we have brisket here.

572
00:24:49,521 --> 00:24:52,524
-You can grill it so quickly.
-Yes.

573
00:24:52,591 --> 00:24:55,627
That's why I keep some brisket at home.

574
00:24:55,694 --> 00:24:57,529
And what's in here?

575
00:24:57,596 --> 00:25:00,131
-We found it.
-Skate from Heuksando.

576
00:25:00,198 --> 00:25:01,733
<i>Fire</i>

577
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,502
Skate from Heuksando.

578
00:25:03,568 --> 00:25:06,438
It doesn't smell funky, though.
Has it been sealed up?

579
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:09,107
Is this skate too? In different parts?

580
00:25:09,174 --> 00:25:12,377
I always eat it raw,

581
00:25:12,444 --> 00:25:16,848
so I wanted to try eating it
in a different form.

582
00:25:16,915 --> 00:25:19,818
I knew I'd be on the show,

583
00:25:19,885 --> 00:25:23,955
-so I decided to come prepared.
-It'll be easy to use.

584
00:25:24,022 --> 00:25:27,125
-I guess different parts taste different.
-I guess so.

585
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:32,297
They're usually divided
into the nose, wings, cheeks, and liver.

586
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:34,132
I found chogochujang.

587
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:37,269
-They come together.
-Let's try some with the sauce.

588
00:25:37,335 --> 00:25:40,805
I got curious and bought
the level-three fermentation.

589
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:44,075
-Level three? There are levels?
-Level three?

590
00:25:44,142 --> 00:25:46,278
-I see.
-It must come in three levels.

591
00:25:46,344 --> 00:25:47,712
-There are three levels.
-Yes.

592
00:25:49,414 --> 00:25:52,317
-So this is how it feels.
-I must mobilize.

593
00:25:52,384 --> 00:25:53,618
It must be strong.

594
00:25:53,685 --> 00:25:55,020
You're the skate expert. Try some.

595
00:25:55,086 --> 00:25:56,588
-How is it?
-How is it?

596
00:25:56,655 --> 00:25:57,956
Do you like it?

597
00:25:58,023 --> 00:25:59,024
Was that what you wanted?

598
00:25:59,090 --> 00:26:03,161
-He's happy.
-That was what he wanted.

599
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:05,564
HOW WILL THE SKATE LOVERS REACT?

600
00:26:05,630 --> 00:26:07,899
It's not so bad. It's not too strong.

601
00:26:07,966 --> 00:26:11,970
-Isn't it just good enough?
-Yes, it's perfectly fermented.

602
00:26:12,037 --> 00:26:16,508
The ones from Busan are
having a tough time trying the skate.

603
00:26:16,575 --> 00:26:18,109
Even Chef Sohyi is avoiding it.

604
00:26:18,176 --> 00:26:20,579
Fermented skate is
something you develop taste for.

605
00:26:20,645 --> 00:26:22,581
It's hard to develop.

606
00:26:22,647 --> 00:26:24,583
-It doesn't smell bad.
-It's not bad.

607
00:26:24,649 --> 00:26:26,718
-j-hope must love it a lot.
-It's okay. It's good.

608
00:26:29,020 --> 00:26:30,021
How is it?

609
00:26:32,190 --> 00:26:33,825
Why does it taste carbonated?

610
00:26:33,892 --> 00:26:35,460
-It's supposed to.
-It's supposed to.

611
00:26:35,527 --> 00:26:38,096
-It's fermented.
-It's the ammonia.

612
00:26:38,163 --> 00:26:40,932
-I get why people like it.
-It's not too strong, right?

613
00:26:40,999 --> 00:26:42,033
But it's not for me.

614
00:26:44,235 --> 00:26:47,372
Chef Rok and Chef Won seem to like it.

615
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:48,974
The fermentation of skate

616
00:26:49,040 --> 00:26:52,077
can help you check the condition

617
00:26:52,143 --> 00:26:54,379
of your bronchial tubes.

618
00:26:54,446 --> 00:26:56,948
-Whoa.
-Yes, j-hope can check the condition

619
00:26:57,015 --> 00:26:58,450
-of his bronchial tubes.
-That's true.

620
00:26:58,516 --> 00:27:01,953
-His bronchial tubes are Grade A.
-Grade A.

621
00:27:02,020 --> 00:27:04,556
He's not coughing at all.

622
00:27:04,623 --> 00:27:06,958
-His bronchial tubes are Grade A.
-Grade A.

623
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:10,061
If he can eat it without coughing,
his bronchial tubes are that healthy.

624
00:27:10,128 --> 00:27:12,764
-He knows skate very well.
-He does.

625
00:27:12,831 --> 00:27:14,032
-Okay, next.
-Yes.

626
00:27:14,099 --> 00:27:15,634
-Fruits, right?
-Fruits.

627
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:19,270
-Mango. He said he liked mango rice.
-Mango.

628
00:27:19,337 --> 00:27:21,439
Yes, I do like mango.

629
00:27:21,506 --> 00:27:22,974
What's this? Peanut butter?

630
00:27:23,041 --> 00:27:24,743
No, I think that's chocolate.

631
00:27:26,211 --> 00:27:28,480
-Chocolate jam.
-You have a sweet tooth.

632
00:27:28,546 --> 00:27:29,914
-This looks special.
-What's this?

633
00:27:29,981 --> 00:27:30,982
It's unique.

634
00:27:31,049 --> 00:27:33,952
-It's something he gathered.
-I found two bags.

635
00:27:34,019 --> 00:27:35,687
-Right?
-Right. I…

636
00:27:35,754 --> 00:27:37,489
He kept these.

637
00:27:37,555 --> 00:27:41,559
It was such a shame to throw out sauces
that come with delivery food.

638
00:27:41,626 --> 00:27:43,028
Those look like amenities.

639
00:27:44,295 --> 00:27:45,797
-Fridge amenities.
-Amenities?

640
00:27:45,864 --> 00:27:47,632
They look like amenities.

641
00:27:47,699 --> 00:27:50,402
You can be a world-class star
by gathering the sauces.

642
00:27:50,969 --> 00:27:54,372
-Is that so? That was the reason?
-Yes, right?

643
00:27:54,439 --> 00:27:55,440
Isn't that the case?

644
00:27:55,507 --> 00:27:57,008
Let's take a look at the freezer.

645
00:27:57,075 --> 00:28:01,880
I see ice cream and bread in the freezer.

646
00:28:01,946 --> 00:28:03,348
And some frozen food.

647
00:28:03,415 --> 00:28:04,849
Chicken nuggets!

648
00:28:04,916 --> 00:28:07,085
I really love
that brand of chicken nuggets.

649
00:28:07,152 --> 00:28:10,455
When I get really hungry at night,

650
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:12,223
I'd whip those up

651
00:28:12,290 --> 00:28:15,160
in a frying pan
or stick them in an air fryer.

652
00:28:15,226 --> 00:28:17,062
Do you warm these up,
then use these sauces?

653
00:28:17,128 --> 00:28:18,229
Yes, you're right.

654
00:28:18,930 --> 00:28:21,032
-Yes, he can use those.
-That's true.

655
00:28:21,099 --> 00:28:25,103
-I make bizarre mixtures with the sauces.
-That's not a bad idea.

656
00:28:25,170 --> 00:28:26,905
His appetite isn't too different from us.

657
00:28:26,971 --> 00:28:28,606
-It's not.
-Right?

658
00:28:28,673 --> 00:28:30,308
-It's similar.
-It is.

659
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:31,676
The lowest shelf.

660
00:28:31,743 --> 00:28:34,913
-I'm seeing some seafood.
-He loves seafood.

661
00:28:34,979 --> 00:28:36,448
These must be shrimp.

662
00:28:36,514 --> 00:28:38,216
No, those aren't shrimp.

663
00:28:38,283 --> 00:28:39,350
-Wait, what's this?
-Wait.

664
00:28:39,417 --> 00:28:41,086
These must be shrimp.

665
00:28:41,152 --> 00:28:43,154
-Wait, what's this?
-Wait. Why are these here?

666
00:28:43,221 --> 00:28:44,222
What's that?

667
00:28:44,289 --> 00:28:47,058
-It's like what you found in my fridge!
-What is it?

668
00:28:47,125 --> 00:28:49,627
He packed up chicken bones
and threw them in the freezer.

669
00:28:49,694 --> 00:28:51,196
Why did you leave these in here?

670
00:28:51,863 --> 00:28:54,165
-Is there a reason?
-Wait, here's why.

671
00:28:54,232 --> 00:28:56,901
I have to throw out bones
with regular waste,

672
00:28:56,968 --> 00:28:59,370
so I have to wait until the bag is full.

673
00:28:59,437 --> 00:29:01,306
I didn't know those were in there.

674
00:29:01,372 --> 00:29:04,008
They could've used it to cook
if he didn't tell us.

675
00:29:04,075 --> 00:29:06,544
I almost used it to make broth.

676
00:29:06,611 --> 00:29:09,514
I almost made chicken broth with that.

677
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:11,082
Bone broth.

678
00:29:11,149 --> 00:29:12,484
Why were those in there?

679
00:29:12,550 --> 00:29:13,551
He'd make broth with that?

680
00:29:13,618 --> 00:29:15,720
That was all for j-hope!

681
00:29:18,490 --> 00:29:20,258
I didn't think you'd find bones.

682
00:29:20,325 --> 00:29:24,729
<i>The first round</i>
<i>with j-hope's ingredients is</i>

683
00:29:24,796 --> 00:29:27,365
fought between Cooking Maniac, Yoon Nam-no

684
00:29:27,432 --> 00:29:31,436
and just a regular old maniac, Kim Poong.

685
00:29:31,503 --> 00:29:34,472
The two maniacs who cook are
up against each other.

686
00:29:34,539 --> 00:29:37,008
-The maniacs are up.
-Yes.

687
00:29:37,075 --> 00:29:38,943
Chef Nam-no is something.

688
00:29:39,010 --> 00:29:43,014
<i>He easily won his first star</i>
<i>during his debut round.</i>

689
00:29:43,081 --> 00:29:46,084
On the other hand,
Artist Poong still has no stars.

690
00:29:46,151 --> 00:29:47,352
Currently, five losses in a row.

691
00:29:47,418 --> 00:29:51,055
At this point in time,
I'm also starting to feel

692
00:29:51,122 --> 00:29:53,158
-rather anxious.
-Of course.

693
00:29:53,224 --> 00:29:55,727
Actually, my family and relatives asked,

694
00:29:55,794 --> 00:29:57,562
"Are you on the show as the comic relief?"

695
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:00,431
-I heard that recently.
-Yes.

696
00:30:00,498 --> 00:30:01,533
I can't go on like this.

697
00:30:01,599 --> 00:30:04,669
I became determined to win a star

698
00:30:04,736 --> 00:30:07,472
and decided to put in
everything I can into this.

699
00:30:07,539 --> 00:30:09,073
-He's very serious.
-He is.

700
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:13,011
First, I wanted to make
Chef Nam-no feel bewildered.

701
00:30:13,077 --> 00:30:14,913
I'll show my professional side
to make him think,

702
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:17,682
"I didn't know Poong could be
so professional."

703
00:30:18,783 --> 00:30:20,418
Who just laughed?

704
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:22,754
-Please don't do that.
-I'm sorry.

705
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:24,656
If you laughed discourteously,
please leave.

706
00:30:24,722 --> 00:30:26,357
I WILL NOT ALLOW
A HINT OF HUMOR TODAY

707
00:30:26,424 --> 00:30:27,559
Let me say something too.

708
00:30:27,625 --> 00:30:28,726
Will you?

709
00:30:28,793 --> 00:30:31,362
If I may quote Chef Hyun-suk,

710
00:30:31,429 --> 00:30:33,264
"I won't cook to get a star."

711
00:30:33,331 --> 00:30:36,367
I'll cook something just for j-hope.

712
00:30:36,434 --> 00:30:38,503
Something just for j-hope.

713
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:39,571
BANG

714
00:30:41,105 --> 00:30:43,274
-I'm so moved.
-He won't cook for a star.

715
00:30:43,341 --> 00:30:44,542
I will

716
00:30:44,609 --> 00:30:46,177
cook for the star.

717
00:30:46,244 --> 00:30:48,513
The star of my heart, j-hope.

718
00:30:52,050 --> 00:30:54,018
-What was that?
-I see.

719
00:30:54,085 --> 00:30:57,522
-Is this a dating show or what?
-It was like <i>I Am SOLO</i>.

720
00:30:57,589 --> 00:30:59,891
But the order isn't easy.

721
00:30:59,958 --> 00:31:02,627
The order is titled, "Skate is on fire."

722
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:05,663
Poong, have you ever cooked with skate?

723
