1197
00:50:56,219 --> 00:50:58,855
I'm glad he didn't put in too much salt.

1198
00:50:58,922 --> 00:51:00,290
He takes another bite.

1199
00:51:00,857 --> 00:51:03,560
j-hope continues to nod.

1200
00:51:03,627 --> 00:51:04,628
This is the best.

1201
00:51:04,694 --> 00:51:06,229
-He said it was the best.
-It's the best.

1202
00:51:06,296 --> 00:51:07,330
This is the best.

1203
00:51:07,397 --> 00:51:09,099
-Yes!
-He said it was the best.

1204
00:51:09,966 --> 00:51:11,268
It's really good.

1205
00:51:11,334 --> 00:51:15,005
Could those who haven't developed a taste
for skate also eat that?

1206
00:51:15,072 --> 00:51:16,073
I wonder.

1207
00:51:16,673 --> 00:51:18,108
-Is that not the case?
-No.

1208
00:51:18,175 --> 00:51:20,610
-That wasn't so.
-I guess it retained the smell.

1209
00:51:20,677 --> 00:51:23,013
I guess I'm one of the fans.

1210
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:25,348
-It doesn't taste foreign.
-Not at all?

1211
00:51:25,415 --> 00:51:30,187
I can even feel the burning sense
like when I drink whiskey.

1212
00:51:30,253 --> 00:51:32,289
-It's on fire.
-It must be on fire.

1213
00:51:32,355 --> 00:51:34,524
People who love whiskey say
it burns on the inside.

1214
00:51:34,591 --> 00:51:38,862
I've had skate often,
but it never felt this way down my throat.

1215
00:51:38,929 --> 00:51:40,630
-Oh, my.
-And it's…

1216
00:51:40,697 --> 00:51:42,265
It's so new to me.

1217
00:51:42,332 --> 00:51:45,202
-So it was a new kind of taste.
-Yes.

1218
00:51:45,268 --> 00:51:48,438
Webtoon Artist Poong's
Sweet and Sour Skate is turning cold.

1219
00:51:48,505 --> 00:51:50,640
-Right.
-Yes.

1220
00:51:50,707 --> 00:51:53,443
Please show him some consideration.

1221
00:51:53,510 --> 00:51:56,213
Next, Webtoon Artist Poong's
Sweet and Sour Skate.

1222
00:51:56,279 --> 00:51:58,381
THEN I'LL GO INTO J-HOPE'S HEART

1223
00:51:58,448 --> 00:52:00,117
LIKE BANG, BANG, SKATE

1224
00:52:00,183 --> 00:52:02,786
LIKE TANG, TANG, SWEET & SOUR

1225
00:52:04,254 --> 00:52:07,657
SPICY, SWEET, AND SOURNESS
OF SWEET AND SOUR SKATE

1226
00:52:09,326 --> 00:52:12,562
SERVED WITH KIMCHI STIR-FRY
TO BALANCE OUT THE GREASINESS

1227
00:52:13,363 --> 00:52:17,367
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
SWEET AND SOUR SKATE

1228
00:52:17,434 --> 00:52:19,436
Do I just eat the skate?

1229
00:52:19,503 --> 00:52:21,538
Yes, it may be hot, though.

1230
00:52:21,605 --> 00:52:22,939
Take a bite and see if it's too hot.

1231
00:52:24,574 --> 00:52:25,709
CRUNCH

1232
00:52:25,775 --> 00:52:27,410
I love the sound.

1233
00:52:28,078 --> 00:52:29,513
It had the crunchy sound.

1234
00:52:30,580 --> 00:52:33,150
His nose is already on fire.

1235
00:52:34,184 --> 00:52:37,087
His nose is on fire!

1236
00:52:38,188 --> 00:52:40,924
ON FIRE WITH THE SMELL OF SKATE

1237
00:52:41,725 --> 00:52:43,193
HE FEELS THE SHARPNESS
IN HIS NOSE

1238
00:52:43,260 --> 00:52:45,061
His nose is on fire.

1239
00:52:46,329 --> 00:52:47,964
He's feeling it.

1240
00:52:48,031 --> 00:52:51,001
-Isn't it more pungent when it's fried?
-It's the strongest

1241
00:52:51,067 --> 00:52:53,870
-when it's deep-fried.
-The smell is the most strong when fried.

1242
00:52:55,038 --> 00:52:56,673
His nose is on fire.

1243
00:52:58,642 --> 00:53:01,978
I love that genuine response.

1244
00:53:03,713 --> 00:53:05,282
Is it stronger when it's deep-fried?

1245
00:53:05,348 --> 00:53:09,786
When it's deep-fried,
the batter won't let the smell escape.

1246
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:12,522
-It looks like he's on fire.
-It keeps it inside.

1247
00:53:12,589 --> 00:53:17,260
So he should dip it more
into the sweet and sour sauce.

1248
00:53:17,327 --> 00:53:19,095
Try the skate and kimchi too.

1249
00:53:19,996 --> 00:53:21,064
Fire!

1250
00:53:21,131 --> 00:53:22,699
It must be really strong.

1251
00:53:23,733 --> 00:53:25,268
He looks so cool.

1252
00:53:25,335 --> 00:53:26,703
-I can't imagine it.
-He's enjoying it.

1253
00:53:26,770 --> 00:53:29,005
-It's hard to imagine.
-But it's

1254
00:53:29,072 --> 00:53:30,373
really good.

1255
00:53:31,508 --> 00:53:33,543
-We don't know who'll win today.
-Kim Poong!

1256
00:53:33,610 --> 00:53:35,645
-We don't know yet.
-Stay hopeful.

1257
00:53:35,712 --> 00:53:38,348
I honestly want to take it home.

1258
00:53:38,415 --> 00:53:40,450
-He wants to take it.
-You did it.

1259
00:53:40,517 --> 00:53:44,487
-He wants it at home.
-I can make that for you every day.

1260
00:53:44,554 --> 00:53:46,556
Follow him around during the world tour.

1261
00:53:46,623 --> 00:53:49,259
I'll follow you around and deep-fry those.

1262
00:53:49,326 --> 00:53:51,494
I also thought these were fried nicely.

1263
00:53:52,762 --> 00:53:56,733
<i>I worked around</i>
<i>Chef Yeon-bok's batter recipe.</i>

1264
00:53:56,800 --> 00:53:59,069
-Try the kimchi too.
-Is he supposed to eat it together?

1265
00:53:59,135 --> 00:54:01,404
You can have it separately
or together, however you like.

1266
00:54:01,471 --> 00:54:03,907
-That's his mother's kimchi.
-Mom's kimchi.

1267
00:54:05,108 --> 00:54:08,111
HOW'S THE KIMCHI STIR-FRY?

1268
00:54:09,212 --> 00:54:11,848
-Why is this here?
-Like the usual skate and kimchi.

1269
00:54:11,915 --> 00:54:13,850
Because people
usually eat skate with kimchi.

1270
00:54:13,917 --> 00:54:15,585
-Because that's usually how it's had?
-Yes.

1271
00:54:15,652 --> 00:54:16,820
Try it with the skate.

1272
00:54:16,886 --> 00:54:19,489
-You said he could have it as he liked.
-You said you didn't care.

1273
00:54:19,556 --> 00:54:21,825
Did I? You should try it together.

1274
00:54:21,891 --> 00:54:23,226
He changes his statement.

1275
00:54:23,293 --> 00:54:24,761
Should I top it with brisket too?

1276
00:54:24,828 --> 00:54:26,830
No, you can just…

1277
00:54:26,896 --> 00:54:28,298
Why did you put brisket in?

1278
00:54:28,365 --> 00:54:29,366
Because of the grease.

1279
00:54:29,432 --> 00:54:32,035
People usually eat
meat, skate, and kimchi together.

1280
00:54:32,102 --> 00:54:33,637
It's not necessary.

1281
00:54:33,703 --> 00:54:36,806
I wanted to add the grease
to add more flavor.

1282
00:54:36,873 --> 00:54:38,141
He tries it with the kimchi.

1283
00:54:38,208 --> 00:54:40,010
It looks like that dish,
kimchi-pizza-sweet and sour pork.

1284
00:54:40,076 --> 00:54:41,177
It looks good.

1285
00:54:42,712 --> 00:54:45,715
Is it better with the kimchi or without?

1286
00:54:47,250 --> 00:54:48,485
-Without…
-Without.

1287
00:54:48,551 --> 00:54:50,153
You shouldn't have made that.

1288
00:54:50,220 --> 00:54:52,856
It only took up your time.

1289
00:54:52,922 --> 00:54:55,125
It does have a certain appeal.

1290
00:54:55,191 --> 00:54:56,459
What's the appeal?

1291
00:54:56,526 --> 00:54:58,728
It's like, "What is this?"

1292
00:54:58,795 --> 00:55:02,265
-"What is this?"
-"How is this made?"

1293
00:55:02,332 --> 00:55:05,201
Try it with the meat too.
This may be the way.

1294
00:55:05,268 --> 00:55:07,170
He tries it like that.

1295
00:55:07,237 --> 00:55:09,639
He topped it with brisket too.

1296
00:55:09,706 --> 00:55:10,907
He eats it so deliciously.

1297
00:55:10,974 --> 00:55:12,008
He does.

1298
00:55:12,075 --> 00:55:14,511
-And he makes it look good.
-Yes, he doesn't hesitate.

1299
00:55:15,578 --> 00:55:18,448
-He had the meat too.
-Is brisket working its magic?

1300
00:55:18,515 --> 00:55:19,883
Yes, it plays a part.

1301
00:55:20,917 --> 00:55:23,353
-He had to eat it with brisket.
-Yes.

1302
00:55:23,420 --> 00:55:25,388
-You're right.
-Right?

1303
00:55:25,455 --> 00:55:27,357
It was my first time making this.

1304
00:55:27,424 --> 00:55:29,359
-That's how we eat it.
-It's better with brisket.

1305
00:55:29,426 --> 00:55:33,396
Yes, that way, it's closer
to how people eat it with kimchi and pork.

1306
00:55:33,463 --> 00:55:37,434
-First, Try Skate <i>Sabayon</i>.
-Try Skate <i>Sabayon</i>.

1307
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:39,736
Please try Chef Nam-no's dish first.

1308
00:55:40,437 --> 00:55:41,438
Mmm.

1309
00:55:42,605 --> 00:55:44,441
-I think it'll be on fire.
-It's strong.

1310
00:55:46,343 --> 00:55:47,644
Gosh.

1311
00:55:48,545 --> 00:55:49,679
FINDS THE COURAGE TO TAKE A BITE

1312
00:55:49,746 --> 00:55:51,614
I get what the tangy sourness is.

1313
00:55:52,582 --> 00:55:57,053
Fermented skate has
that distinct pungent flavor,

1314
00:55:57,120 --> 00:55:58,988
<i>but the </i>sabayon <i>covers it up</i>

1315
00:55:59,055 --> 00:56:02,959
<i>and adds more flavor</i>
<i>to give it that smoothness.</i>

1316
00:56:03,026 --> 00:56:06,429
I was surprised that the skate had
such interesting texture and flavor.

1317
00:56:06,496 --> 00:56:10,333
<i>It's fun to eat this chewy yet soft meat.</i>

1318
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:13,303
I thought he played a smart move

1319
00:56:13,370 --> 00:56:18,708
<i>because he made the sauce with </i>hallabong
<i>and topped it with basil at the end.</i>

1320
00:56:18,775 --> 00:56:22,612
It added that fragrant note nicely.
It was delicious.

1321
00:56:22,679 --> 00:56:25,315
He's so eloquent too.

1322
00:56:26,149 --> 00:56:27,951
Right? Yes.

1323
00:56:28,017 --> 00:56:29,953
Listen to what he said,
not how he said it.

1324
00:56:30,019 --> 00:56:32,255
-She didn't hear what he said.
-Listen to what he said.

1325
00:56:32,322 --> 00:56:36,092
-He has a nice profile when he speaks.
-Jeez.

1326
00:56:36,159 --> 00:56:41,431
Next, Webtoon Artist Poong's dish.

1327
00:56:41,998 --> 00:56:43,666
It doesn't smell at all.

1328
00:56:44,234 --> 00:56:46,236
THEN WHAT ABOUT THE TASTE?

1329
00:56:46,302 --> 00:56:47,771
-Sweet and sour.
-Sweet and sour.

1330
00:56:50,273 --> 00:56:51,775
It looks good.

1331
00:56:51,841 --> 00:56:53,376
-It does.
-Yes.

1332
00:56:53,443 --> 00:56:55,078
COUGHING

1333
00:56:55,145 --> 00:56:58,648
The sauce goes well with the skate.

1334
00:56:58,715 --> 00:57:00,417
It's a nice mix.

1335
00:57:00,483 --> 00:57:01,684
I was a bit surprised.

1336
00:57:01,751 --> 00:57:04,721
I watched the process in the closest seat.

1337
00:57:04,788 --> 00:57:07,023
Yes, everything was a mess.

1338
00:57:07,090 --> 00:57:10,393
I was surprised with the batter.
It's really delicious.

1339
00:57:10,460 --> 00:57:12,128
He learned well from Chef Yeon-bok.

1340
00:57:12,195 --> 00:57:14,164
I don't think it should be good,
but it is.

1341
00:57:14,230 --> 00:57:16,199
Isn't it odd?
It feels like it shouldn't be, but it is.

1342
00:57:16,266 --> 00:57:17,967
My heart says no, but my heart says yes.

1343
00:57:18,034 --> 00:57:19,602
HIS FLAVOR WAS A TOTAL PRO!

1344
00:57:19,669 --> 00:57:21,704
It was a wonder that he made this.

1345
00:57:21,771 --> 00:57:25,408
It's j-hope's turn to choose.

1346
00:57:25,475 --> 00:57:27,577
-This is close.
-It must be so hard.

1347
00:57:27,644 --> 00:57:29,145
Press one for Yoon Nam-no.

1348
00:57:30,046 --> 00:57:31,915
Press two for Kim Poong.

1349
00:57:32,882 --> 00:57:36,686
Please make your decision
and press the button!

1350
00:57:37,654 --> 00:57:39,122
-j-hope!
-Who will it be?

1351
00:57:39,189 --> 00:57:40,790
Do I really have to choose?

1352
00:57:40,857 --> 00:57:41,858
They were both so good.

1353
00:57:41,925 --> 00:57:43,593
-Who will it be?
-Who was on fire?

1354
00:57:43,660 --> 00:57:46,062
-I won't be able to choose.
-Who was on fire?

1355
00:57:46,129 --> 00:57:48,665
-Fire!
-Which one set your nose on fire?

1356
00:57:48,731 --> 00:57:49,766
-I pressed it.
-He did!

1357
00:57:49,833 --> 00:57:52,035
He pressed it.

1358
00:57:52,101 --> 00:57:53,169
My palms are sweaty.

1359
00:57:53,236 --> 00:57:56,506
Let's find out who the winner is. Show us!

1360
00:57:56,573 --> 00:57:59,275
-Who will it be?
-Skate is on fire.

1361
00:57:59,342 --> 00:58:01,811
-Fire!
-Fire!

1362
00:58:01,878 --> 00:58:05,648
Will Poong break his losing streak
and win his first star?

1363
00:58:05,715 --> 00:58:10,687
Or will Chef Nam-no take two wins in a row
right after his debut round?

1364
00:58:10,753 --> 00:58:13,957
Who did j-hope choose?

1365
00:58:14,791 --> 00:58:18,394
Whose skate dish was better?

1366
00:58:19,062 --> 00:58:20,363
-j-hope!
-Who will it be?

1367
00:58:20,430 --> 00:58:22,165
Tell us, j-hope!

1368
00:58:25,068 --> 00:58:26,436
Tell us, j-hope!

1369
00:58:27,704 --> 00:58:29,005
Kim Poong!

1370
00:58:29,072 --> 00:58:30,540
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
SWEET AND SOUR SKATE WINS

1371
00:58:30,607 --> 00:58:34,711
Kim Poong! Kim Poong wins!

1372
00:58:35,778 --> 00:58:37,447
Kim Poong finally wins!

1373
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:41,251
-Gosh.
-It's your first win!

1374
00:58:43,419 --> 00:58:44,420
ALL SMILES

1375
00:58:44,487 --> 00:58:46,823
-It was really tough to choose.
-Yes.

1376
00:58:46,890 --> 00:58:52,495
I wanted to try eating skate
in a different form,

1377
00:58:52,562 --> 00:58:55,431
so in that aspect,
they both gave me what I wanted.

1378
00:58:55,498 --> 00:58:58,067
But my focus was this.

1379
00:58:58,134 --> 00:59:03,573
I didn't know skate could taste so good
when it was deep-fried.

1380
00:59:03,640 --> 00:59:05,742
It suited my taste perfectly.

1381
00:59:05,808 --> 00:59:09,512
It was a dish I'd love to order and have

1382
00:59:09,579 --> 00:59:12,582
when I returned from my world tour.

1383
00:59:12,649 --> 00:59:15,818
Why would you order it then?
Let him tag along in your tour.

1384
00:59:15,885 --> 00:59:20,156
-I'll tag along.
-Will you go with him?

1385
00:59:20,223 --> 00:59:22,025
Will you go instead of doing this show?

1386
00:59:22,091 --> 00:59:26,529
The show isn't the issue!
He needs my dish during his world tour.

1387
00:59:26,596 --> 00:59:29,332
Can you give us your song again?

1388
00:59:29,399 --> 00:59:32,735
<i>Then I'll go into j-hope's heart</i>

1389
00:59:32,802 --> 00:59:36,706
<i>Like bang, bang, skate</i>

1390
00:59:36,773 --> 00:59:38,341
<i>Sweet tanghulu</i>

1391
00:59:39,709 --> 00:59:42,979
He proudly receives his first star.

1392
00:59:43,046 --> 00:59:44,581
You've done so well.

1393
00:59:44,647 --> 00:59:47,283
Look how he is.

1394
00:59:47,350 --> 00:59:50,286
He looks so proud. Proud Poong.

1395
00:59:50,353 --> 00:59:52,755
Can you do the song again?

1396
00:59:52,822 --> 00:59:56,726
<i>Like bang, bang, skate</i>

1397
00:59:56,793 --> 01:00:01,130
Congratulations! Artist Poong wins a star.

1398
01:00:02,432 --> 01:00:06,669
This is the second round
with j-hope's ingredients.

1399
01:00:06,736 --> 01:00:10,940
Chef Double Stars with good vibes,
Chef Son Jong-won

1400
01:00:11,007 --> 01:00:15,378
versus Chef Kwon Sung-jun,
the winner of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1401
01:00:15,445 --> 01:00:16,946
This is another huge match.

1402
01:00:17,013 --> 01:00:18,247
I'm looking forward to it.

1403
01:00:18,314 --> 01:00:22,418
We thought <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
must not be the show for Chef Sung-jun.

1404
01:00:22,485 --> 01:00:25,521
But he wins two rounds in a row

1405
01:00:25,588 --> 01:00:31,327
as soon as he passes on
his pan, Sylvia, to Poong.

1406
01:00:31,394 --> 01:00:35,765
So? Did losing Sylvia
actually help you win stars?

1407
01:00:35,832 --> 01:00:38,701
I'm not the type who clings to my exes.

1408
01:00:38,768 --> 01:00:41,137
Gosh, Sylvia.

1409
01:00:41,204 --> 01:00:43,306
He never looks back.

1410
01:00:43,806 --> 01:00:45,208
-Sorry?
-Is he dating someone?

1411
01:00:45,274 --> 01:00:46,275
No.

1412
01:00:46,909 --> 01:00:49,345
The name of his frying pan was Sylvia.

1413
01:00:49,412 --> 01:00:50,413
It was his pan.

1414
01:00:50,480 --> 01:00:53,750
Poong also took his first win

1415
01:00:53,816 --> 01:00:56,019
-after he abandoned Sylvia.
-Yes.

1416
01:00:56,085 --> 01:00:58,554
-<i>Sylvia's curse.</i>
-<i>Don't call it a curse.</i>

1417
01:00:58,621 --> 01:01:03,593
I heard Chef Jong-won said
he'd do anything to win today.

1418
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:05,962
My mother called me

1419
01:01:06,029 --> 01:01:08,665
while I was on my way home
after the shoot last week.

1420
01:01:08,731 --> 01:01:11,267
She asked, "How was the shoot?"

1421
01:01:11,334 --> 01:01:13,002
I said, "I lost,

1422
01:01:13,069 --> 01:01:17,807
but I did my best
and showed everything I prepared."

1423
01:01:17,874 --> 01:01:19,409
But she responded by saying,

1424
01:01:19,475 --> 01:01:21,377
"Stop doing it
if you'll continue to lose."

1425
01:01:21,444 --> 01:01:23,513
Don't do it if you'll lose.

1426
01:01:23,579 --> 01:01:25,081
She was that sad.

1427
01:01:25,148 --> 01:01:27,550
Chef Jong-won,
please say something to your mother.

1428
01:01:29,085 --> 01:01:31,954
Do that. "I'm sorry your son is
a big shot at <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>, Mom."

1429
01:01:32,755 --> 01:01:33,856
THAT SOUNDS SO COOL

1430
01:01:33,923 --> 01:01:36,359
Your son is such a big shot on the show.
I'm sorry, Mom.

1431
01:01:36,426 --> 01:01:39,662
I'm sorry your son is a big shot
at <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>, Mom.

1432
01:01:40,229 --> 01:01:41,864
THE SINGER IS HAPPY

1433
01:01:41,931 --> 01:01:44,701
-That was a good move for the owner.
-Yes.

1434
01:01:44,767 --> 01:01:46,602
It may not seem like much,

1435
01:01:46,669 --> 01:01:49,172
-but he'll notice you more.
-That can happen.

1436
01:01:49,238 --> 01:01:51,140
-He'll lean toward you.
-Yes.

1437
01:01:51,207 --> 01:01:53,976
If you win today,
you have to give me your business card.

1438
01:01:55,244 --> 01:01:57,580
You have to give me your cell number.

1439
