-Are they married?

1532
01:05:44,840 --> 01:05:46,876
-We're getting to know each other.
-It's just her.

1533
01:05:46,943 --> 01:05:50,613
-Is it one-way?
-Yes, it's one-way.

1534
01:05:50,680 --> 01:05:53,716
-That's a sad story.
-It's sad, but I'll put up with it.

1535
01:05:53,783 --> 01:05:55,184
I have a question.

1536
01:05:55,251 --> 01:05:58,120
He borrowed a hair dryer from me.

1537
01:05:58,187 --> 01:05:59,588
-A hair dryer?
-Yes.

1538
01:05:59,655 --> 01:06:02,692
-I prepared this secret weapon.
-There's a hair dryer.

1539
01:06:02,758 --> 01:06:04,360
-He let me use it.
-That's the hair dryer.

1540
01:06:04,427 --> 01:06:06,929
-Did he ask his stylist?
-It's…

1541
01:06:08,030 --> 01:06:09,899
This is the hair dryer j-hope uses.

1542
01:06:09,966 --> 01:06:11,300
-Yes.
-Is that so?

1543
01:06:11,367 --> 01:06:15,204
I didn't know why he borrowed it.
I found it fascinating.

1544
01:06:15,271 --> 01:06:16,272
Is he using it to cook?

1545
01:06:16,339 --> 01:06:18,607
-Is he doing sugar craft?
-He uses a hair dryer to cook?

1546
01:06:18,674 --> 01:06:19,675
What do you need a hair dryer for?

1547
01:06:19,742 --> 01:06:22,345
-You're using it to cook, right?
-Yes.

1548
01:06:22,411 --> 01:06:25,548
Will you dry your hair in the middle?

1549
01:06:25,614 --> 01:06:28,718
-To put on a performance in the round?
-Yes.

1550
01:06:28,784 --> 01:06:30,519
-In the middle.
-An appearance check.

1551
01:06:30,586 --> 01:06:33,522
-An appearance check.
-So he'll use a hair dryer.

1552
01:06:33,589 --> 01:06:35,191
It's the dessert round.

1553
01:06:35,257 --> 01:06:37,860
<i>Why do you shake up my heart?</i>

1554
01:06:37,927 --> 01:06:40,196
Let us begin the round.

1555
01:06:42,531 --> 01:06:43,766
This is a big match.

1556
01:06:43,833 --> 01:06:46,936
He doesn't think he can lose
when it comes to dessert.

1557
01:06:47,003 --> 01:06:50,973
The self-proclaimed father of tiramisu,
the tiramisu expert,

1558
01:06:51,040 --> 01:06:53,042
Chef Kwon Sung-jun is up.

1559
01:06:53,809 --> 01:06:56,645
But this chef doesn't think
he can lose against Sung-jun.

1560
01:06:56,712 --> 01:07:01,484
The Michelin double-star technician is
here to open up a new world for tiramisu.

1561
01:07:01,550 --> 01:07:03,986
Chef Son Jong-won is up as well.

1562
01:07:04,053 --> 01:07:06,756
Who'll become
the prince of tiramisu today?

1563
01:07:06,822 --> 01:07:10,926
Let us begin the 15-minute cook-off!

1564
01:07:10,993 --> 01:07:12,495
Let us begin!

1565
01:07:13,462 --> 01:07:15,898
A BATTLE TO MAKE
THE BEST PICK-ME-UP TIRAMISU

1566
01:07:15,965 --> 01:07:17,967
The two are starting.

1567
01:07:18,034 --> 01:07:20,870
-What's that?
-Coffee. Espresso.

1568
01:07:20,936 --> 01:07:24,340
This is a tiramisu war, so it means
the loser is bad at making tiramisu.

1569
01:07:24,407 --> 01:07:26,142
-You're right.
-Yes.

1570
01:07:26,208 --> 01:07:27,676
This is a battle of pride.

1571
01:07:27,743 --> 01:07:29,378
-What's that?
-Whoa.

1572
01:07:29,445 --> 01:07:32,114
-He's adding snacks.
-The chocolate snack.

1573
01:07:32,181 --> 01:07:33,983
I get it. You are supposed to

1574
01:07:34,050 --> 01:07:36,552
lay the foundation
with cookies soaked in espresso syrup.

1575
01:07:36,619 --> 01:07:38,387
I see.

1576
