1667
01:11:28,117 --> 01:11:29,485
It's giving him trouble.

1668
01:11:29,551 --> 01:11:33,222
That's how you make ricotta cheese
by separating the milk serum.

1669
01:11:33,289 --> 01:11:35,190
-He strains it on a cloth.
-Will he have enough time?

1670
01:11:35,257 --> 01:11:38,360
-Right? It has to cool down.
-It has to cool down.

1671
01:11:38,427 --> 01:11:41,664
-The time will be up.
-It won't be easy to do it with just milk.

1672
01:11:41,730 --> 01:11:43,565
WHAT'S THAT SMOKE?

1673
01:11:43,632 --> 01:11:45,734
Is the chocolate burnt?

1674
01:11:45,801 --> 01:11:47,236
The chocolate is burnt.

1675
01:11:47,303 --> 01:11:48,604
I'm seeing smoke!

1676
01:11:48,671 --> 01:11:50,406
HE FINISHES WHIPPING THE YOLK

1677
01:11:50,472 --> 01:11:54,877
A microwave melts chocolate in high heat,
so it can burn the chocolate.

1678
01:11:54,943 --> 01:11:56,378
He put it in the microwave.

1679
01:11:56,445 --> 01:11:59,281
-He's using the hair dryer!
-The hair dryer!

1680
01:11:59,348 --> 01:12:00,449
SWOOSH

1681
01:12:00,516 --> 01:12:02,685
Chef Jong-won is using a hair dryer!

1682
01:12:02,751 --> 01:12:04,553
He's doing it with a hair dryer.

1683
01:12:04,620 --> 01:12:08,357
If he uses a hair dryer,
it'll melt more evenly.

1684
01:12:10,125 --> 01:12:13,329
-He uses a hair dryer.
-It won't work in the microwave.

1685
01:12:13,395 --> 01:12:14,897
-What's that?
-What's he doing?

1686
01:12:14,963 --> 01:12:16,065
-Decorations.
-He's making feathers.

1687
01:12:16,131 --> 01:12:19,168
I've seen that on YouTube too!

1688
01:12:19,234 --> 01:12:22,004
-It's all on YouTube. He'll freeze that.
-Why is he doing it on the counter?

1689
01:12:22,071 --> 01:12:24,073
He puts it over film

1690
01:12:24,139 --> 01:12:27,209
to make feather shapes on it.

1691
01:12:27,276 --> 01:12:30,646
It wasn't just the counter.
He's doing it on the film.

1692
01:12:30,713 --> 01:12:32,614
Gosh, Jong-won.

1693
01:12:32,681 --> 01:12:34,783
They do look like feathers.

1694
01:12:34,850 --> 01:12:38,053
He took everyone's attention.

1695
01:12:38,120 --> 01:12:41,824
Sung-jun is putting up a lonely fight.

1696
01:12:41,890 --> 01:12:43,492
No one is watching him.

1697
01:12:43,559 --> 01:12:45,928
Jong-won takes all cameras!

1698
01:12:45,994 --> 01:12:48,263
-We've never seen that before.
-We haven't.

1699
01:12:48,330 --> 01:12:52,468
I think he's worthy
of appearing on <i>What on Earth!</i>

1700
01:12:52,534 --> 01:12:54,436
He's putting on awesome performances.

1701
01:12:54,503 --> 01:12:56,038
The shapes are different

1702
01:12:56,105 --> 01:12:59,875
-because of the tremor as he continues.
-He's trembling.

1703
01:12:59,942 --> 01:13:01,677
He made 12 feathers.

1704
01:13:02,544 --> 01:13:05,214
IT'S TIME TO BRING THEM HOME

1705
01:13:05,914 --> 01:13:09,618
HE ROLLS IT
AND SEALS IT WITH TAPE

1706
01:13:10,552 --> 01:13:12,354
DAZED…

1707
01:13:13,055 --> 01:13:16,825
7. HARDEN FEATHER-SHAPED
CHOCOLATE IN THE FREEZER

1708
01:13:16,892 --> 01:13:20,229
-The feathers are in the freezer too.
-Yes.

1709
01:13:20,295 --> 01:13:22,431
He needs to make the cream now.

1710
01:13:22,498 --> 01:13:24,099
Is it time to make cream?

1711
01:13:24,166 --> 01:13:26,902
Jong-won just nodded.

1712
01:13:26,969 --> 01:13:28,670
KWON SUNG-JUN BEGINS
TO MAKE LASSI

1713
01:13:29,171 --> 01:13:30,339
GREEK YOGURT

1714
01:13:30,906 --> 01:13:33,242
COCONUT MILK, MILK

1715
01:13:33,308 --> 01:13:35,377
Is he cutting an apple mango?

1716
01:13:35,444 --> 01:13:37,079
j-hope's favorite, apple mango.

1717
01:13:37,146 --> 01:13:38,447
-Yes.
-You're right.

1718
01:13:40,382 --> 01:13:42,851
-With the skin?
-He'll blend it with the skin?

1719
01:13:42,918 --> 01:13:44,019
-With the skin?
-With the skin?

1720
01:13:45,454 --> 01:13:47,489
4. BLEND GREEK YOGURT,
COCONUT MILK,

1721
01:13:47,556 --> 01:13:49,558
MILK, AND APPLE MANGO
TO MAKE LASSI

1722
01:13:49,625 --> 01:13:50,859
He's adding ice cream.

1723
01:13:50,926 --> 01:13:52,127
Ice cream.

1724
01:13:52,694 --> 01:13:55,664
BECOME DELICIOUS

1725
01:13:56,465 --> 01:13:58,534
USING TWO HANDS?

1726
01:13:59,034 --> 01:14:01,804
He's wringing something out.

1727
01:14:01,870 --> 01:14:04,540
-He's wringing something.
-He has to wring ricotta cheese out.

1728
01:14:04,606 --> 01:14:07,543
The milk serum needs to be
completely separated

1729
01:14:07,609 --> 01:14:10,245
until the water underneath turns clear.

1730
01:14:10,312 --> 01:14:12,314
But it didn't boil enough, so…

1731
01:14:12,381 --> 01:14:13,916
He couldn't learn that.

1732
01:14:13,982 --> 01:14:16,552
That's why it takes a while
to strain the mixture.

1733
01:14:16,618 --> 01:14:19,855
-I guess he didn't learn that.
-I think he made some, though.

1734
01:14:21,156 --> 01:14:23,292
-It's a bit…
-This won't be easy.

1735
01:14:23,358 --> 01:14:26,628
-The problem is time.
-He'll use it up trying to wring that out.

1736
01:14:26,695 --> 01:14:29,264
We're about halfway done.

1737
01:14:29,331 --> 01:14:30,499
It's disadvantageous for Sung-jun.

1738
01:14:30,566 --> 01:14:32,468
-Oh, no.
-He has the disadvantage.

1739
01:14:32,534 --> 01:14:36,705
How long will Sung-jun wring that out?

1740
01:14:36,772 --> 01:14:39,308
-It's as if he's making herbal medicine.
-Right?

1741
01:14:39,374 --> 01:14:42,010
Will he have ricotta cheese
when he opens that cloth?

1742
01:14:42,077 --> 01:14:43,445
Yes.

1743
01:14:44,613 --> 01:14:47,282
SIMPLE SYRUP, SUGAR AND WATER

1744
01:14:47,349 --> 01:14:48,350
ADD SIMPLE SYRUP

1745
01:14:49,184 --> 01:14:53,489
5. WHIP EGG YOLK WHILE POURING
SIMPLE SYRUP INSIDE

1746
01:14:56,091 --> 01:14:58,060
THE DOUBLE-BOILED EGG YOLKS

1747
01:14:58,694 --> 01:14:59,795
SON JONG-WON USES
A HAND MIXER TOO

1748
01:14:59,862 --> 01:15:01,964
That's a new machine.

1749
01:15:02,030 --> 01:15:04,132
I'm seeing lots of machines today.

1750
01:15:04,199 --> 01:15:06,168
They're using high-tech machines.

1751
01:15:06,235 --> 01:15:08,937
They need lots of machines
to make dessert.

1752
01:15:09,004 --> 01:15:10,339
What's he doing now?

1753
01:15:10,405 --> 01:15:13,675
He's mixing mascarpone cheese
with egg yolks.

1754
01:15:13,742 --> 01:15:15,777
That's a typical tiramisu recipe.

1755
01:15:15,844 --> 01:15:17,579
-I see.
-The recipe for tiramisu.

1756
01:15:17,646 --> 01:15:19,448
-He had mascarpone?
-Yes.

1757
01:15:19,515 --> 01:15:21,416
It was in the fridge.

1758
01:15:21,483 --> 01:15:23,785
But he chooses not to use it?

1759
01:15:23,852 --> 01:15:26,722
The mascarpone will make a big difference.

1760
01:15:26,788 --> 01:15:29,224
-They keep using machines.
-Yes.

1761
01:15:31,360 --> 01:15:34,496
It must be because it's dessert.
Is that the cheese? No.

1762
01:15:34,563 --> 01:15:39,334
-It has to be mixed in until it's ivory.
-I see.

1763
01:15:39,401 --> 01:15:41,303
HE HAS 7 MINUTES LEFT

1764
01:15:42,070 --> 01:15:44,773
THE EGG YOLKS TURNED IVORY

1765
01:15:44,840 --> 01:15:46,208
It looks right.

1766
01:15:46,275 --> 01:15:48,777
Sung-jun is opening the cloth!

1767
01:15:48,844 --> 01:15:51,847
-Does he have ricotta cheese?
-Is there ricotta cheese?

1768
01:15:54,416 --> 01:15:56,652
-Is there ricotta cheese?
-What's that?

1769
01:15:56,718 --> 01:15:58,186
What is that?

1770
01:15:58,253 --> 01:16:00,556
-What is that?
-What happened?

1771
01:16:00,622 --> 01:16:03,058
-What is that?
-What's going on?

1772
01:16:03,125 --> 01:16:04,927
-What are you doing?
-Ricotta!

1773
01:16:04,993 --> 01:16:07,462
-What is that?
-It's coming.

1774
01:16:07,529 --> 01:16:10,365
-What is that?
-He's ripping it out from the cloth.

1775
01:16:10,432 --> 01:16:12,134
-You must've wrung it out too much.
-It's not that.

1776
01:16:12,200 --> 01:16:13,602
-It didn't clot.
-He took it off too quickly.

1777
01:16:13,669 --> 01:16:16,772
The protein comes out
when the milk serum is fully separated.

1778
01:16:16,838 --> 01:16:19,708
-But if it's not boiled enough…
-That's all? That's too little.

1779
01:16:19,775 --> 01:16:23,345
…it just leaves with the water
in the milk form.

1780
01:16:23,412 --> 01:16:25,380
That won't taste like tiramisu.

1781
01:16:25,447 --> 01:16:27,683
This is bad. Sung-jun faces a crisis.

1782
01:16:27,749 --> 01:16:31,787
What's important is that he wanted
to make cream with ricotta cheese.

1783
01:16:31,853 --> 01:16:35,257
But without enough cheese,
it'll be like runny syrup.

1784
01:16:35,324 --> 01:16:36,992
-You're right.
-Like runny syrup.

1785
01:16:37,059 --> 01:16:38,794
Just like yogurt or water.

1786
01:16:38,860 --> 01:16:41,897
RATHER RUNNY RICOTTA CREAM
IS FINISHED!

1787
01:16:43,165 --> 01:16:46,602
HE HAD BEEN BOILING COFFEE
AND CHOCOLATE SNACKS

1788
01:16:46,668 --> 01:16:49,905
THE COFFEE AND CHOCOLATE DOUGH

1789
01:16:50,906 --> 01:16:52,307
HE GETS A FORCING BAG READY

1790
01:16:52,374 --> 01:16:54,710
THE MASCARPONE GOES IN

1791
01:16:59,815 --> 01:17:03,485
-He's putting on another performance!
-The master performer!

1792
01:17:03,552 --> 01:17:06,388
He was like Hulk Hogan!

1793
01:17:06,455 --> 01:17:09,291
-What are you squeezing out?
-What is it?

1794
01:17:09,358 --> 01:17:10,726
He's determined.

1795
01:17:10,792 --> 01:17:12,628
He wanted his mom to be proud.

1796
01:17:12,694 --> 01:17:13,996
Jong-won is determined.

1797
01:17:14,062 --> 01:17:16,331
-Five minutes.
-Eun-ji, please go out on the field.

1798
01:17:16,398 --> 01:17:17,466
I'll go now.

1799
01:17:17,532 --> 01:17:19,234
-Eun-ji, to the field.
-Oh, my.

1800
01:17:20,836 --> 01:17:21,903
I'll go.

1801
01:17:22,471 --> 01:17:25,007
Oh, my! It smells so sweet over here!

1802
01:17:25,073 --> 01:17:26,975
-Already?
-Yes.

1803
01:17:27,042 --> 01:17:28,477
He's more good-looking from the back.

1804
01:17:28,543 --> 01:17:33,015
She has an ulterior motive.
Eun-ji shows her ulterior motive.

1805
01:17:33,081 --> 01:17:35,083
-She's just bothering him.
-Bothering?

1806
01:17:35,150 --> 01:17:36,918
Don't get just Jong-won on camera.

1807
01:17:37,486 --> 01:17:38,520
BALLOONS, OUT

1808
01:17:39,021 --> 01:17:41,156
They're hardened. The balloons are hard.

1809
01:17:41,223 --> 01:17:43,191
Guys, the balloon!

1810
01:17:44,826 --> 01:17:46,028
Whoa.

1811
01:17:47,396 --> 01:17:49,831
HE JUST HAS
TO PULL THE BALLOON OUT

1812
01:17:49,898 --> 01:17:52,668
-The balloon.
-It's stuck on the chocolate!

1813
01:17:52,734 --> 01:17:55,003
-Will it come out?
-No.

1814
01:17:55,070 --> 01:17:56,638
-It's coming off.
-Will it break?

1815
01:17:56,705 --> 01:17:57,706
What's going on?

1816
01:17:57,773 --> 01:17:59,708
-Shh.
-No, be careful.

1817
01:17:59,775 --> 01:18:01,209
Whoa.

1818
01:18:01,276 --> 01:18:03,378
-What will happen?
-It's Jong-won's biggest crisis!

1819
01:18:03,445 --> 01:18:06,081
-The chocolate won't come off.
-Will he crash down?

1820
01:18:06,581 --> 01:18:09,217
-Why won't it come off?
-Did it freeze too quickly?

1821
01:18:09,284 --> 01:18:11,987
-His hands are trembling.
-It's coming off.

1822
01:18:12,054 --> 01:18:14,923
-Will he have to eat the balloon too?
-It's coming off.

1823
01:18:17,192 --> 01:18:18,193
SIGH…

1824
01:18:19,294 --> 01:18:20,996
It came off.

1825
01:18:21,063 --> 01:18:24,132
-There's some left.
-There are pieces on it.

1826
01:18:24,199 --> 01:18:26,635
He lost a minute and 30 seconds
doing this.

1827
01:18:26,702 --> 01:18:29,705
-He's finally using a knife.
-He's taking it off with a knife.

1828
01:18:29,771 --> 01:18:31,840
-He's done.
-He's done.

1829
01:18:31,907 --> 01:18:33,208
His hands are trembling so much.

1830
01:18:33,275 --> 01:18:34,710
My gosh.

1831
01:18:34,776 --> 01:18:37,512
He's already starting to serve it.

1832
01:18:39,881 --> 01:18:43,051
7. ADD HALLABONG ZEST
TO THE RICOTTA CREAM

1833
01:18:43,618 --> 01:18:45,187
HE BEGINS TO SERVE IT
IN A WIDE GLASS

1834
01:18:45,253 --> 01:18:46,254
CHOCOLATE COOKIE

1835
01:18:46,755 --> 01:18:48,056
ESPRESSO

1836
01:18:48,123 --> 01:18:50,459
8. SOAK CHOCOLATE COOKIE IN
ESPRESSO AND PUT IT IN THE GLASS

1837
01:18:50,525 --> 01:18:52,227
But it looks like

1838
01:18:52,294 --> 01:18:54,162
the texture isn't too…

1839
01:18:55,530 --> 01:18:56,565
It's all part of the plan.

1840
01:18:56,631 --> 01:18:59,568
It looks too runny.

1841
01:18:59,634 --> 01:19:01,069
-Eun-ji!
-Yes?

1842
01:19:01,136 --> 01:19:02,704
Can you give that a taste?

1843
01:19:02,771 --> 01:19:03,905
-I'll try this.
-Give it a try.

1844
01:19:03,972 --> 01:19:05,707
Will it shake up your heart?

1845
01:19:05,774 --> 01:19:07,509
That's the tiramisu cream.

1846
01:19:07,576 --> 01:19:09,544
-It looked a bit runny.
-Yes.

1847
01:19:09,611 --> 01:19:11,413
The consistency doesn't look solid.

1848
01:19:11,480 --> 01:19:13,281
Will it shake up her heart?

1849
01:19:13,782 --> 01:19:15,584
Eun-ji!

1850
01:19:15,650 --> 01:19:17,018
WILL IT SHAKE UP J-HOPE'S HEART?

1851
01:19:19,588 --> 01:19:23,291
-It will shake him up!
-It will shake up his heart!

1852
01:19:23,358 --> 01:19:24,493
And completely.

1853
01:19:24,559 --> 01:19:26,128
It went into the freezer.

1854
01:19:26,194 --> 01:19:28,797
It's so good.

1855
01:19:28,864 --> 01:19:30,065
They have two minutes left.

1856
01:19:30,132 --> 01:19:31,867
-It's so good.
-You have two minutes left.

1857
01:19:31,933 --> 01:19:33,435
You have two minutes left.

1858
01:19:35,003 --> 01:19:36,705
-You have two minutes left.
-The leaves.

1859
01:19:36,772 --> 01:19:38,907
The leaves? No. What are those?

1860
01:19:38,974 --> 01:19:40,976
-Wings, right?
-Feathers?

1861
01:19:41,042 --> 01:19:44,780
Feathers? Goose feathers? What are those?

1862
01:19:44,846 --> 01:19:48,283
-I think he'll put it on like feathers.
-Those?

1863
01:19:48,984 --> 01:19:50,852
SUNG-JUN SERVES THE LASSI

1864
01:19:51,553 --> 01:19:55,524
10. STRAIN MANGO LASSI IN A
STRAINER AND SERVE IT IN A GLASS

1865
01:19:58,460 --> 01:20:01,129
He's doing the dirty plating method.

1866
01:20:01,196 --> 01:20:04,933
That chocolate looks almost too sweet.

1867
01:20:05,000 --> 01:20:09,037
He's doing
the dirty plating method on purpose.

1868
01:20:09,104 --> 01:20:11,072
It's the Seongsu-dong style.

1869
01:20:11,139 --> 01:20:12,440
And the straw.

1870
01:20:13,108 --> 01:20:14,576
What's he doing now?

1871
01:20:14,643 --> 01:20:17,913
-Sung-jun puts it in the fridge.
-To cool it.

1872
01:20:17,979 --> 01:20:18,980
CLICK

1873
01:20:20,649 --> 01:20:23,418
HE HEATS THE TIP OF THE KNIFE
WITH THE TORCH

1874
01:20:23,952 --> 01:20:26,121
He's now operating!

1875
01:20:26,188 --> 01:20:28,290
It's like <i>The Trauma Code: Heroes on Call</i>.

1876
01:20:29,758 --> 01:20:30,859
Be careful.

1877
01:20:30,926 --> 01:20:32,360
<i>The Cooking Code</i>!

1878
01:20:32,427 --> 01:20:33,862
You have no time.

1879
01:20:33,929 --> 01:20:35,997
-You have a minute and 30 seconds.
-A minute and 30 seconds.

1880
01:20:36,064 --> 01:20:37,265
HE ADDS THE FEATHER TEXTURE

1881
01:20:37,332 --> 01:20:39,000
I can't get closer
because of their passion.

1882
01:20:40,202 --> 01:20:42,337
HE PLANS TO USE EVERY SECOND

1883
01:20:42,404 --> 01:20:44,306
Sung-jun is now plating his dessert.

1884
01:20:44,372 --> 01:20:45,774
He's writing something…

1885
01:20:45,841 --> 01:20:47,309
-What is it?
-…with the chocolate.

1886
01:20:47,943 --> 01:20:49,477
-What's that?
-He's plating it.

1887
01:20:49,544 --> 01:20:50,879
Jong-won is done too.

1888
01:20:50,946 --> 01:20:52,514
What's that?

1889
01:20:52,581 --> 01:20:54,783
Chef Jong-won,
you have a minute and 15 seconds.

1890
01:20:54,850 --> 01:20:57,853
You have about a minute now.

1891
01:20:57,919 --> 01:20:59,321
What's that now?

1892
01:21:00,255 --> 01:21:02,190
He's sticking a candle on the plate.

1893
01:21:02,257 --> 01:21:03,525
Look at his hand.

1894
01:21:03,592 --> 01:21:05,827
It's his birthday tomorrow.

1895
01:21:05,894 --> 01:21:08,230
HE'S THE BONG JOON-HO
OF THE SHOW!

1896
01:21:08,296 --> 01:21:09,698
-Oh, no.
-Fifty seconds.

1897
01:21:09,764 --> 01:21:12,167
-Fifty seconds.
-He uses a candle for his birthday.

1898
01:21:12,234 --> 01:21:13,468
-Fifty seconds.
-You have fifty seconds.

1899
01:21:13,535 --> 01:21:16,471
CHOCOLATE BAR, COFFEE AND
CHOCOLATE DOUGH, CHOCOLATE SHELL

1900
01:21:16,538 --> 01:21:19,241
-Forty seconds.
-You have forty seconds!

1901
01:21:20,642 --> 01:21:22,844
-The cream looks good.
-Forty seconds.

1902
01:21:22,911 --> 01:21:25,881
-You must focus and finish up.
-Forty seconds.

1903
01:21:26,414 --> 01:21:27,582
Thirty seconds.

1904
01:21:27,649 --> 01:21:28,850
You can do this.

1905
01:21:28,917 --> 01:21:30,285
-Twenty seconds.
-You can do it.

1906
01:21:31,686 --> 01:21:33,655
KWON SUNG-JUN FINISHES UP TOO!

1907
01:21:34,923 --> 01:21:36,524
PUTS THE STRAW IN

1908
01:21:36,591 --> 01:21:38,526
Hurry. Take that for him.

1909
01:21:39,194 --> 01:21:40,528
JONG-WON FINISHES
THE DECORATION TOO!

1910
01:21:41,663 --> 01:21:43,732
You really have ten seconds. Ten.

1911
01:21:43,798 --> 01:21:45,433
-Nine. Eight.
-Eight.

1912
01:21:45,500 --> 01:21:47,202
-Seven.
-Seven.

1913
01:21:47,269 --> 01:21:49,271
-Six. Five.
-Hurry up!

1914
01:21:49,337 --> 01:21:51,740
-Eight. Seven.
-Eight. Seven.

1915
01:21:51,806 --> 01:21:53,775
-Six. Five.
-Hurry up!

1916
01:21:53,842 --> 01:21:57,712
-Four. Three. Two. One.
-Four. Three. Two. One.

1917
01:21:57,779 --> 01:21:58,947
It's over.

1918
01:22:01,082 --> 01:22:02,484
Who hit the bell first?

1919
01:22:02,550 --> 01:22:06,187
-Chef Jong-won hit it first.
-It was Chef Jong-won.

1920
01:22:06,254 --> 01:22:07,822
-Whoa.
-Whoa.

1921
01:22:07,889 --> 01:22:09,925
I couldn't even talk to them.

1922
01:22:09,991 --> 01:22:12,093
-They were so focused.
-They were, and so passionate.

1923
01:22:12,160 --> 01:22:13,929
-My gosh.
-But…

1924
01:22:14,996 --> 01:22:18,667
The chefs finished
making these desserts for j-hope.

1925
01:22:18,733 --> 01:22:20,302
They finished safely.

1926
01:22:22,037 --> 01:22:25,140
What do you think about the presentation?
Which do you like more?

1927
01:22:25,206 --> 01:22:29,177
I was craving something sweet
because I love desserts that much.

1928
01:22:29,244 --> 01:22:30,245
I'm dying to try it.

1929
01:22:30,312 --> 01:22:32,847
Especially that one. That's art.

1930
01:22:32,914 --> 01:22:34,783
-Chef Jong-won's?
-Yes.

1931
01:22:34,849 --> 01:22:37,686
How did he make this in 15 minutes?

1932
01:22:37,752 --> 01:22:39,254
-Right?
-Yes.

1933
01:22:39,321 --> 01:22:40,322
It's such a wonder.

1934
01:22:40,889 --> 01:22:43,758
CHOCOLATE SHELL MADE
WITH A BALLOON

1935
01:22:44,259 --> 01:22:47,696
FILLED WITH THICK CREAM
AND CHOCOLATE FEATHERS

1936
01:22:49,497 --> 01:22:51,533
A CANDLE
TO CELEBRATE HIS BIRTHDAY

1937
01:22:52,934 --> 01:22:55,971
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S
TIRAMI-CHELIN

1938
01:22:56,037 --> 01:22:59,207
-May I serve it myself?
-Will you do it yourself?

1939
01:22:59,941 --> 01:23:01,643
J-HOPE IS TOUCHED

1940
01:23:01,710 --> 01:23:05,647
This isn't an ordinary occasion.
He's coming over. He's a special guest.

1941
01:23:05,714 --> 01:23:06,715
This is big.

1942
01:23:06,781 --> 01:23:08,249
I'm so moved.

1943
01:23:08,316 --> 01:23:10,652
-It's because he's a special guest.
-Yes.

1944
01:23:11,186 --> 01:23:14,689
-He has everything in his pocket.
-It's your birthday tomorrow.

1945
01:23:14,756 --> 01:23:16,358
You said it was your birthday.

1946
01:23:17,692 --> 01:23:21,029
I feel like I'm celebrating
at a fine dining restaurant.

1947
01:23:21,096 --> 01:23:24,499
They do this for you
when you say it's your birthday.

1948
01:23:24,566 --> 01:23:27,802
-After a delicious meal, right?
-They dimmed the lights too.

1949
01:23:27,869 --> 01:23:31,339
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU

1950
01:23:31,406 --> 01:23:34,509
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU

1951
01:23:34,576 --> 01:23:37,946
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, DEAR J-HOPE

1952
01:23:38,013 --> 01:23:40,215
Happy birthday to you!

1953
01:23:40,882 --> 01:23:42,984
HE MAKES A WISH

1954
01:23:43,051 --> 01:23:45,053
Happy birthday to you!

1955
01:23:45,120 --> 01:23:47,322
THE STUDIO BECOMES HEARTWARMING

1956
01:23:47,389 --> 01:23:51,593
That was a considerate move
from Chef Jong-won.

1957
01:23:51,659 --> 01:23:53,928
-He may get extra points.
-He may.

1958
01:23:53,995 --> 01:23:55,330
I think I'll add lots of points.

1959
01:23:55,397 --> 01:23:58,700
-Lots of points.
-The candle.

1960
01:23:58,767 --> 01:24:00,402
How do I eat this?

1961
01:24:00,468 --> 01:24:03,338
Use the spoon
to go deep into the tiramisu.

1962
01:24:03,405 --> 01:24:05,940
You'll see some feathers on top.

1963
01:24:06,007 --> 01:24:08,743
I wanted to make you feel like
you were flying.

1964
01:24:09,444 --> 01:24:10,645
FLUTTERING

1965
01:24:10,712 --> 01:24:12,714
Are you giving him wings?

1966
01:24:15,583 --> 01:24:18,753
-He gave me wings.
-Just before his world tour.

1967
01:24:18,820 --> 01:24:21,389
-Just before his solo career.
-It's so moving.

1968
01:24:21,456 --> 01:24:25,293
It's so significant.
His words are having an impact.

1969
01:24:25,360 --> 01:24:27,395
He looks quite shaken up.

1970
01:24:28,363 --> 01:24:30,165
It just needs to be delicious.

1971
01:24:33,501 --> 01:24:34,502
MM-HMM?

1972
01:24:35,136 --> 01:24:37,572
This is Tirami-Chelin.

1973
01:24:39,040 --> 01:24:41,276
-So? How is it?
-Should I go in deeper?

1974
01:24:41,342 --> 01:24:43,812
-It's in there.
-You'll find the crunchy inside.

1975
01:24:43,878 --> 01:24:44,879
I should have that too.

1976
01:24:44,946 --> 01:24:46,614
He'd be shaken up quite a lot.

1977
01:24:46,681 --> 01:24:48,483
How many stars
does Michelin Guide give out?

1978
01:24:48,550 --> 01:24:50,118
-Up to three.
-Up to three.

1979
01:24:50,185 --> 01:24:52,120
Tell us if it's one, two, or three.

1980
01:24:52,187 --> 01:24:55,023
Tirami-Chelin.
He just bit onto something big.

1981
01:24:55,090 --> 01:24:57,392
How many stars will you give him?

1982
01:24:58,393 --> 01:24:59,394
WHY IS HE ONLY SMILING?

1983
01:24:59,461 --> 01:25:00,495
Are you shaken up?

1984
01:25:00,562 --> 01:25:02,597
What is it? Why are you nodding?

1985
01:25:02,664 --> 01:25:04,933
-He can't talk because it's that good.
-Because it's that good?

1986
01:25:05,800 --> 01:25:08,136
THE 3RD GIGGLE

1987
01:25:08,203 --> 01:25:09,671
-It must be good.
-Yes.

1988
01:25:09,737 --> 01:25:12,540
It's a taste that lifts you up.

1989
01:25:12,607 --> 01:25:16,010
Tiramisu actually means
to pick me up, or cheer me up.

1990
01:25:16,077 --> 01:25:18,146
-It fits perfectly.
-It does.

1991
01:25:18,213 --> 01:25:19,914
He's looking more cheerful.

1992
01:25:19,981 --> 01:25:23,084
-It's worth three stars.
-Three stars!

1993
01:25:23,151 --> 01:25:24,319
Three stars!

1994
01:25:25,120 --> 01:25:27,856
Tirami-Chelin gets three stars.

1995
01:25:29,357 --> 01:25:30,925
But there is one thing.

1996
01:25:30,992 --> 01:25:34,696
-The chocolate base is kind of strong.
-Is it strong?

1997
01:25:34,762 --> 01:25:38,032
-Yes.
-It needs that bitter espresso aftertaste.

1998
01:25:38,099 --> 01:25:41,636
I thought it'd be like that,

1999
01:25:41,703 --> 01:25:46,074
but it felt like
something other than tiramisu.

2000
01:25:46,141 --> 01:25:50,345
-That's just Tirami-Chelin.
-It's not the tiramisu you know.

2001
01:25:50,411 --> 01:25:53,548
But what I can say is
that it's really good.

2002
01:25:53,615 --> 01:25:54,983
-It's really good.
-It's good.

2003
01:25:55,049 --> 01:25:57,519
The thing is, tiramisu is
an Italian dessert.

2004
01:25:57,585 --> 01:26:00,622
But this is Tirami-Chelin,
a French dessert.

2005
01:26:00,688 --> 01:26:04,959
It'll be different
from an authentic tiramisu.

2006
01:26:05,527 --> 01:26:06,928
CONVINCED

2007
01:26:06,995 --> 01:26:10,365
Chef Sohyi has already decided
whom she'd take back to Austria.

2008
01:26:10,431 --> 01:26:13,968
-That's why she's covering for him.
-She made the decision.

2009
01:26:14,035 --> 01:26:16,271
Jong-won is the one who'll go to Austria.

2010
01:26:16,337 --> 01:26:18,239
Chef Sohyi was shaken up too.

2011
01:26:18,306 --> 01:26:19,807
Yes, it happens.

2012
01:26:19,874 --> 01:26:23,044
-It was really good.
-Was it really?

2013
01:26:23,611 --> 01:26:28,316
TIRAMISU TEXTURE MADE WITH MILK
SERVED WITH APPLE MANGO LASSI

2014
01:26:29,551 --> 01:26:32,654
CHEF KWON SUNG-JUN'S
TIRAMISU AGAIN

2015
01:26:32,720 --> 01:26:34,856
May I serve it myself too?

2016
01:26:34,923 --> 01:26:37,192
-He wants to serve it.
-He'll do it himself.

2017
01:26:37,258 --> 01:26:39,160
-Yes.
-He learned that quickly.

2018
01:26:39,727 --> 01:26:40,929
What is this?

2019
01:26:40,995 --> 01:26:44,933
This was the chocolate
I drew on that dish.

2020
01:26:44,999 --> 01:26:47,268
-It was on the plastic.
-Wait.

2021
01:26:47,335 --> 01:26:49,971
-What is this?
-It was just this before.

2022
01:26:50,038 --> 01:26:51,706
-j-hope would know.
-Hey, wait.

2023
01:26:51,773 --> 01:26:53,675
-What?
-Are you serving that now?

2024
01:26:53,741 --> 01:26:55,810
-It was just the tiramisu.
-It wasn't there before.

2025
01:26:55,877 --> 01:26:58,580
He can't use that.
You didn't put it out before.

2026
01:26:58,646 --> 01:27:00,448
-Where did you get it?
-You did it after it was over.

2027
01:27:00,515 --> 01:27:01,583
You don't have to eat it.

2028
01:27:01,649 --> 01:27:03,818
What are you suddenly talking about?

2029
01:27:03,885 --> 01:27:07,822
-He made this urgently after it was over.
-Yes.

2030
01:27:07,889 --> 01:27:09,691
That's like a candle.

2031
01:27:09,757 --> 01:27:11,226
j-hope will understand.

2032
01:27:11,292 --> 01:27:12,994
That's the logo for BTS.

2033
01:27:13,061 --> 01:27:17,432
If you flip it around,
it becomes a logo for our fandom, ARMY.

2034
01:27:17,498 --> 01:27:19,367
I think he did that for me.

2035
01:27:19,434 --> 01:27:21,202
Yes, as an ARMY,

2036
01:27:21,269 --> 01:27:22,770
I flipped it around.

2037
01:27:23,438 --> 01:27:24,772
ARMY

2038
01:27:24,839 --> 01:27:27,041
My gosh. This is a bit…

2039
01:27:27,108 --> 01:27:29,010
Chef Jong-won, what do you think?

2040
01:27:29,077 --> 01:27:30,878
-Should I take it off?
-Will you let him do this?

2041
01:27:30,945 --> 01:27:35,016
It's the important for the fridge owner
to experience it in its full meaning.

2042
01:27:35,083 --> 01:27:36,084
I knew it.

2043
01:27:36,951 --> 01:27:39,487
-He's such a nice guy.
-He is.

2044
01:27:39,554 --> 01:27:40,888
He's more intrigued!

2045
01:27:40,955 --> 01:27:42,824
Jong-won gets more kudos!

2046
01:27:42,890 --> 01:27:44,425
He's such a nice guy.

2047
01:27:44,492 --> 01:27:47,729
-He would've lost it if he said no.
-Yes, he would've lost it.

2048
01:27:48,496 --> 01:27:51,132
He's not just Chef Good Vibes,
but he's Chef Good Guy.

2049
01:27:51,199 --> 01:27:53,801
-He's such a good guy.
-He is.

2050
01:27:53,868 --> 01:27:54,936
Chef Good Guy.

2051
01:27:55,003 --> 01:27:58,406
Will this shake him up too?
He'd be shaken up like a Polaroid picture.

2052
01:27:58,473 --> 01:28:00,908
There's cookie-like texture in the middle.

2053
01:28:01,643 --> 01:28:02,910
<i>I'm shaken up</i>

2054
01:28:02,977 --> 01:28:06,080
There are cookies inside,
so scoop that up and eat it together.

2055
01:28:06,147 --> 01:28:07,815
I soaked the cookies with coffee.

2056
01:28:07,882 --> 01:28:09,851
He made that dolphin noise. "Mmm!"

2057
01:28:09,917 --> 01:28:13,354
-There's something inside. He went in.
-Look at the texture.

2058
01:28:13,421 --> 01:28:14,822
-That's like tiramisu.
-Try it with the cream.

2059
01:28:14,889 --> 01:28:17,859
-It was good.
-Was it good when you tried it?

2060
01:28:19,093 --> 01:28:20,862
That's a solid tiramisu.

2061
01:28:20,928 --> 01:28:23,097
HAPPY

2062
01:28:24,599 --> 01:28:27,635
His face says it all.

2063
01:28:28,369 --> 01:28:30,571
-My gosh.
-"My gosh."

2064
01:28:30,638 --> 01:28:34,108
Why did you put mango in here?

2065
01:28:34,175 --> 01:28:38,846
I didn't use mango there.
I added some hallabong zest there.

2066
01:28:38,913 --> 01:28:41,916
It'll taste more refreshing.
You won't get sick of it.

2067
01:28:41,983 --> 01:28:44,719
I guess it added this strong scent.

2068
01:28:44,786 --> 01:28:47,021
-So <i>hallabong</i> skin?
-Yes, some <i>hallabong</i> skin.

2069
01:28:47,088 --> 01:28:51,092
-I added some yogurt to add freshness.
-To add freshness.

2070
01:28:51,159 --> 01:28:53,528
Can you call that tiramisu, though?

2071
01:28:53,594 --> 01:28:58,533
Actually, authentic tiramisu is
actually on the runny side.

2072
01:28:58,599 --> 01:29:00,902
It's not completely creamy.

2073
01:29:00,968 --> 01:29:03,404
TIME TO TRY THE LASSI

2074
01:29:04,672 --> 01:29:07,308
-You can eat it with the chocolate.
-He scooped it up.

2075
01:29:07,375 --> 01:29:10,545
Try it with the chocolate and the cereal.

2076
01:29:10,611 --> 01:29:13,514
-I feel like I'm in Seongsu-dong.
-Yes, right?

2077
01:29:13,581 --> 01:29:15,516
It's like a place in Seongsu-dong.

2078
01:29:15,583 --> 01:29:18,252
It's because he's a millennial.

2079
01:29:18,319 --> 01:29:19,454
-You made it rough.
-Yes.

2080
01:29:21,622 --> 01:29:23,091
-It's good.
-It must be.

2081
01:29:23,157 --> 01:29:25,827
He just drooled.
Is it refreshing? Sweet? What's it like?

2082
01:29:25,893 --> 01:29:28,396
This tastes like

2083
01:29:28,463 --> 01:29:30,932
the original tiramisu that I know

2084
01:29:30,998 --> 01:29:35,036
with a bit of refreshing taste.

2085
01:29:35,103 --> 01:29:37,171
There's a scoop of freshness.

2086
01:29:37,238 --> 01:29:40,341
Yes, so it doesn't feel unfamiliar.

2087
01:29:40,408 --> 01:29:41,609
It's worthy of its name.

2088
01:29:41,676 --> 01:29:46,147
This is just…
I feel like I'm in Seongsu-dong.

2089
01:29:48,216 --> 01:29:49,817
Were you shaken up with this?

2090
01:29:49,884 --> 01:29:52,487
-Yes.
-There's something that hits him.

2091
01:29:52,553 --> 01:29:55,857
-This is so hard. I'm in trouble.
-It's hard.

2092
01:29:55,923 --> 01:29:59,026
First, let's try Tirami-Chelin.

2093
01:29:59,093 --> 01:30:02,563
WHAT'S TIRAMI-CHELIN LIKE?

2094
01:30:03,197 --> 01:30:05,066
-It's excellent.
-It's good.

2095
01:30:05,133 --> 01:30:06,567
The balance.

2096
01:30:06,634 --> 01:30:08,469
-It's rich.
-The texture.

2097
01:30:08,536 --> 01:30:11,139
I love how the texture is like jelly.

2098
01:30:11,205 --> 01:30:12,740
It has this rich taste.

2099
01:30:12,807 --> 01:30:16,544
As soon as you have a bite,
it tastes rich and full.

2100
01:30:16,611 --> 01:30:18,179
It's that rich.

2101
01:30:18,246 --> 01:30:20,381
Let's try Chef Sung-jun's dessert.

2102
01:30:21,182 --> 01:30:24,118
WHAT WILL TIRAMISU
AGAIN TASTE LIKE?

2103
01:30:24,952 --> 01:30:26,220
It stands out.

2104
01:30:26,287 --> 01:30:28,256
The tanginess adds that flavor.

2105
01:30:28,322 --> 01:30:30,458
-They're completely different.
-Completely.

2106
01:30:30,525 --> 01:30:32,160
If I may say a word each,

2107
01:30:32,226 --> 01:30:34,829
it'd be richness and freshness.

2108
01:30:34,896 --> 01:30:36,631
Chef Jong-won's dessert is rich,

2109
01:30:36,697 --> 01:30:38,766
and Chef Sung-jun's dessert is fresh.

2110
01:30:38,833 --> 01:30:41,969
-He has to make a decision.
-How will he pick just one?

2111
01:30:44,439 --> 01:30:45,440
It still tastes good, right?

2112
01:30:46,007 --> 01:30:49,610
The texture that captured me the most was

2113
01:30:49,677 --> 01:30:51,579
this one.

2114
01:30:51,646 --> 01:30:53,815
-It's more like tiramisu we know.
-Yes.

2115
01:30:53,881 --> 01:30:57,518
But this is new,
yet the form is exactly like tiramisu.

2116
01:30:57,585 --> 01:31:00,021
-These two are distinctly different.
-He looks puzzled.

2117
01:31:00,087 --> 01:31:02,757
-It's very hard to pick one.
-I see.

2118
01:31:02,824 --> 01:31:05,526
Press one for Son Jong-won.

2119
01:31:05,593 --> 01:31:08,095
Press two for Kwon Sung-jun.

2120
01:31:08,162 --> 01:31:11,299
Please press the button, j-hope!

2121
01:31:11,365 --> 01:31:13,067
<i>Why do you shake up my heart?</i>

2122
01:31:13,134 --> 01:31:14,402
This is so hard too.

2123
01:31:14,469 --> 01:31:16,070
-It is.
-It's hard.

2124
01:31:16,137 --> 01:31:19,607
-Pick one who shook up your heart harder.
-Harder than the other.

2125
01:31:19,674 --> 01:31:22,310
SHAKE SHAKE

2126
01:31:24,078 --> 01:31:25,112
Who shook you up?

2127
01:31:25,179 --> 01:31:27,215
I could never pick one.

2128
01:31:27,281 --> 01:31:28,549
-Did you press one?
-I did.

2129
01:31:28,616 --> 01:31:31,152
-He pressed it. My gosh.
-He made his decision.

2130
01:31:31,219 --> 01:31:34,755
Wait, Chef Jong-won needs to win
for me to get his business card.

2131
01:31:34,822 --> 01:31:36,657
WILL SHE GET IT?

2132
01:31:36,724 --> 01:31:40,294
Who was chosen by j-hope?

2133
01:31:40,361 --> 01:31:43,464
Let us find out the result
to this dessert war!

2134
01:31:43,531 --> 01:31:45,266
-Who is it?
-Show us!

2135
01:31:45,333 --> 01:31:47,201
Who did j-hope choose?

2136
01:31:47,268 --> 01:31:49,637
-Why do you shake up my heart?
-Why do you shake up my heart?

2137
01:31:49,704 --> 01:31:52,406
-Is it Sung-jun or Jong-won?
-Why?

2138
01:31:52,473 --> 01:31:54,942
Is it Italian or French?

2139
01:31:55,009 --> 01:31:57,445
Who did j-hope choose?

2140
01:31:57,512 --> 01:31:58,513
Who is it?

2141
01:31:58,579 --> 01:32:01,749
-Who shook up his heart?
-Who is it?

2142
01:32:01,816 --> 01:32:03,384
Show us the result!

2143
01:32:04,886 --> 01:32:05,887
Who is it?

2144
01:32:07,488 --> 01:32:08,489
Son Jong-won!

2145
01:32:08,556 --> 01:32:10,324
CHEF SON JONG-WON'S
TIRAMI-CHELIN WINS

2146
01:32:10,391 --> 01:32:11,526
Son Jong-won!

2147
01:32:12,527 --> 01:32:15,329
Chef Jong-won was chosen.

2148
01:32:17,398 --> 01:32:20,835
Thank you.

2149
01:32:20,902 --> 01:32:23,104
-Why?
-I'll get his business card.

2150
01:32:24,505 --> 01:32:27,241
It suited my order well in many ways,

2151
01:32:27,308 --> 01:32:30,912
and he also shook up my heart
in different aspects.

2152
01:32:30,978 --> 01:32:33,114
The presentation and all.

2153
01:32:33,180 --> 01:32:34,682
It looks so cool.

2154
01:32:34,749 --> 01:32:37,218
<i>And he remembered it was my birthday.</i>

2155
01:32:37,285 --> 01:32:40,354
-I was quite moved.
-I see.

2156
01:32:40,421 --> 01:32:42,456
And his cooking process too.

2157
01:32:42,523 --> 01:32:43,724
He put on that show.

2158
01:32:43,791 --> 01:32:46,727
-The way he was focused…
-Yes, he looks cool.

2159
01:32:46,794 --> 01:32:48,930
-Come on.
-Yes, he looked really cool.

2160
01:32:48,996 --> 01:32:50,131
<i>It can't be helped.</i>

2161
01:32:50,197 --> 01:32:54,669
<i>Chef Jong-won gets additional points</i>
<i>for those moments.</i>

2162
01:32:54,735 --> 01:32:57,505
I wanted to see Chef Sung-jun too,

2163
01:32:57,572 --> 01:32:59,840
but he was covered up by Poong.

2164
01:32:59,907 --> 01:33:02,209
-I couldn't see him.
-Me?

2165
01:33:02,276 --> 01:33:04,478
-Why didn't you move?
-You should've moved.

2166
01:33:04,545 --> 01:33:07,748
-I'm so sorry.
-You have a huge head too.

2167
01:33:07,815 --> 01:33:12,153
But when it came to the flavor,
they were in completely different styles.

2168
01:33:12,219 --> 01:33:14,488
So I decided to choose something

2169
01:33:14,555 --> 01:33:16,891
-that had more meaning for me.
-I see.

2170
01:33:16,958 --> 01:33:19,126
-That's how he shakes up your heart.
-Yes.

2171
01:33:19,193 --> 01:33:22,196
Just now, Chef Sung-jun looked relieved

2172
01:33:22,263 --> 01:33:24,065
when he just lost.

2173
01:33:24,131 --> 01:33:26,000
-Why?
-I don't know why, though.

2174
01:33:26,067 --> 01:33:27,068
Were you relieved?

2175
01:33:27,134 --> 01:33:28,402
The thing is,

2176
01:33:28,469 --> 01:33:30,171
I cheated.

2177
01:33:31,238 --> 01:33:34,942
I wouldn't have been called back next week
if I won this round.

2178
01:33:35,943 --> 01:33:38,212
-<i>He has a good conscience.</i>
-<i>He told the truth.</i>

2179
01:33:38,279 --> 01:33:39,981
He's so genuine.

2180
01:33:40,047 --> 01:33:43,818
We'll let you off because of your honesty.

2181
01:33:43,884 --> 01:33:46,887
Chef Jong-won, can we hear it from you?

2182
01:33:46,954 --> 01:33:49,256
I'm going to call my mom

2183
01:33:49,323 --> 01:33:51,058
during the break.

2184
01:33:51,626 --> 01:33:53,127
CLAPPING FOR HIS GOOD HEART

2185
01:33:53,194 --> 01:33:56,130
That's nice. "I'm sorry, Mom."

2186
01:33:56,197 --> 01:33:59,367
Chef Jong-won gets his second star!

2187
01:33:59,433 --> 01:34:00,701
Congratulations.

2188
01:34:00,768 --> 01:34:02,970
It's from j-hope.

2189
01:34:03,037 --> 01:34:05,373
-He should call his mom soon.
-Two stars.

2190
01:34:05,439 --> 01:34:09,143
HE GETS DOUBLE STARS
ON CHEF & MY FRIDGE TOO

2191
01:34:09,210 --> 01:34:10,211
BRUTAL

2192
01:34:10,277 --> 01:34:13,381
I loved how wild he was.

2193
01:34:13,447 --> 01:34:16,350
-I heard, "Deok-su?"
-"Deok-su."

2194
01:34:16,417 --> 01:34:17,652
Do you want me to send you that?

2195
01:34:18,452 --> 01:34:20,321
He has a twist.

2196
01:34:20,388 --> 01:34:22,857
He has such a kind heart on the inside.

2197
01:34:22,923 --> 01:34:24,859
Can Chef Kang-rok be a villain?

2198
01:34:24,925 --> 01:34:26,761
-He can do it.
-He can do it.

2199
01:34:26,827 --> 01:34:28,796
-You can do it.
-You can do it, Chef Kang-rok.

2200
01:34:29,730 --> 01:34:30,931
THE LONG-AWAITED RIVALS!

2201
01:34:30,998 --> 01:34:33,634
<i>It's titled Italian,</i>
<i>so I do not want to lose.</i>

2202
01:34:33,701 --> 01:34:36,003
<i>Italian cuisine is my root.</i>

2203
01:34:36,070 --> 01:34:37,304
AN UNDEFEATED WINNING STREAK

2204
01:34:37,371 --> 01:34:38,472
I won't let it go.

2205
01:34:39,707 --> 01:34:41,742
The two reunite as enemies
after two years.

2206
01:34:41,809 --> 01:34:43,544
<i>I'll show you how to do it.</i>

2207
01:34:43,611 --> 01:34:44,945
<i>She's so cool.</i>

2208
01:34:45,012 --> 01:34:46,947
<i>She'll run out of time.</i>

2209
01:34:47,615 --> 01:34:48,816
<i>He was on the show first.</i>

2210
01:34:48,883 --> 01:34:50,551
<i>You've grown a lot and become bold.</i>

2211
01:34:50,618 --> 01:34:52,653
I need to use UNICHEF.

2212
01:34:52,720 --> 01:34:54,088
What do you need?

2213
01:34:54,155 --> 01:34:55,923
HOW WILL
THE TEACHER-PUPIL BATTLE END?

2214
01:35:08,869 --> 01:35:13,874
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
